1
00:01:18,348 --> 00:01:21,830


2
00:01:21,914 --> 00:01:25,084
The French tried to build a canal here before the Americans.

3
00:01:25,344 --> 00:01:27,471
At the height of their effort, 500 workers...

4
00:01:27,523 --> 00:01:31,663
...were dying every week from malaria and yellow fever.

5
00:01:31,997 --> 00:01:35,104
They couldn't come up with cemetery space fast enough...

6
00:01:35,844 --> 00:01:39,442
...not to mention the morale problem all those crosses would have made.

7
00:01:39,984 --> 00:01:42,966
So they bought shiploads of vinegar in Cuba...

8
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:46,928
...and in each barrel, they sealed one corpse.

9
00:01:47,220 --> 00:01:50,484
And then they sold them as medical cadavers all over Europe.

10
00:01:51,151 --> 00:01:52,642
And for a while,

11
00:01:52,726 --> 00:01:54,968
that was their principal source of profit.

12
00:01:55,166 --> 00:01:56,292
You see,

13
00:01:56,563 --> 00:02:00,598
this place has always had a special way of dealing...

14
00:02:00,828 --> 00:02:02,631
...with both profit and death.

15
00:02:09,138 --> 00:02:12,996


16
00:02:23,621 --> 00:02:26,124
As some of you may have heard,

17
00:02:26,155 --> 00:02:29,721
there is a hurricane warning tonight.

18
00:02:29,836 --> 00:02:33,850
Well, Rangers do not wait on good weather.

19
00:02:33,944 --> 00:02:39,439
Rangers do not wait for a bright, sunshiny day.

20
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:45,143
Oh, no. Rangers are trained to operate in the worst possible conditions...

21
00:02:45,247 --> 00:02:49,606
...and take said conditions and turn them against their enemy.

22
00:02:49,699 --> 00:02:53,015
You each have one rifle,

23
00:02:53,015 --> 00:02:55,903
one sidearm and one white phosphorus grenade.

24
00:02:55,945 --> 00:02:58,427
This is a live E and E,

25
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:00,992
so please keep those weapons safetied...

26
00:03:01,023 --> 00:03:05,476
...so as not to shoot off your nonexistent dicks.

27
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:11,961
The rally point is a bunker two clicks north of the LZ.

28
00:03:11,972 --> 00:03:14,818
You will split into teams of two.

29
00:03:14,839 --> 00:03:19,698
Each designated area has 20 reactive targets.

30
00:03:19,709 --> 00:03:22,774
The first team to get all 20

31
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:25,704
and reach the rally point wins.

32
00:03:25,715 --> 00:03:28,613
Anything goes pear-shaped out there,

33
00:03:28,624 --> 00:03:31,126
you pop white and radio in.

34
00:03:31,157 --> 00:03:34,744
I will be in each area monitoring your progress.

35
00:03:34,755 --> 00:03:38,884
If I see anybody drag ass...

36
00:03:38,894 --> 00:03:42,721
...I swear to God, you will swim the canal.

37
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:53,357


38
00:03:54,483 --> 00:03:56,631


39
00:03:58,216 --> 00:04:02,105


40
00:04:11,396 --> 00:04:15,045
- Where is the original pickup point? - About two klicks up the valley.

41
00:04:15,264 --> 00:04:17,860
So this was a Ranger training team?

42
00:04:17,902 --> 00:04:19,737
When were they due?

43
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,511
They missed contact six hours ago.

44
00:04:22,542 --> 00:04:25,597
Colonel Styles, that doesn't necessarily mean

45
00:04:25,608 --> 00:04:27,349
anything in a storm like this.

46
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:30,258
No, it wouldn't be any wonder if they were delayed.

47
00:04:35,951 --> 00:04:37,484
I'm not seeing them.

48
00:04:38,590 --> 00:04:40,289
I'm gonna have to come back around.

49
00:04:40,790 --> 00:04:45,252
Wait a minute. Wait a minute, I'm coming around to your side.

50
00:04:45,263 --> 00:04:48,078
We got one... No, maybe two.

51
00:04:48,099 --> 00:04:50,080
Wait, I think he's carrying somebody. Is he hurt?

52
00:04:50,132 --> 00:04:51,978
All right, let's get down there.

53
00:05:11,894 --> 00:05:13,134
What is that?

54
00:05:15,929 --> 00:05:17,556
Is that live fire?

55
00:05:26,846 --> 00:05:28,181
Christ, they're shooting at each other.

56
00:05:28,275 --> 00:05:30,078
Get us on the ground. Now!

57
00:05:45,323 --> 00:05:47,231
I've got a bleeder down here.

58
00:05:47,294 --> 00:05:48,712
A little suction down there.

59
00:05:48,931 --> 00:05:50,349
There it is.

60
00:05:51,058 --> 00:05:52,518
That's enough!

61
00:05:53,331 --> 00:05:55,406
You went out with your sergeant

62
00:05:55,468 --> 00:05:58,565
and six men last night on an exercise.

63
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,776
You came back a few men light.

64
00:06:01,641 --> 00:06:03,967
Four, to be precise.

65
00:06:06,511 --> 00:06:08,388
Where are they?

66
00:06:34,737 --> 00:06:36,270
Not in this lifetime.

67
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:41,650
Captain...

68
00:06:42,682 --> 00:06:44,486
...if you don't make progress on this,

69
00:06:44,549 --> 00:06:46,843
we'll have Washington crawling all over us.

70
00:06:46,884 --> 00:06:48,167
What did he write?

71
00:06:53,328 --> 00:06:55,237
"I'll only talk to a Ranger. Someone from off-post."

72
00:06:55,289 --> 00:06:56,988
Let me see it.

73
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:02,390
It's a stall tactic. Nothing more.

74
00:07:19,886 --> 00:07:21,794
Give him what he wants. I know somebody.

75
00:07:21,857 --> 00:07:23,411
Sir, I am confident that I can handle this.

76
00:07:23,484 --> 00:07:25,016
And I'm not.

77
00:07:29,792 --> 00:07:39,281


78
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,481
Oh, God.

79
00:07:41,971 --> 00:07:51,282


80
00:07:53,889 --> 00:07:56,141
Ten, nine, eight, seven,

81
00:07:56,183 --> 00:07:57,987
six, five, four,

82
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:59,718
three, two, one.

83
00:07:59,791 --> 00:08:01,417
Hello.

84
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:02,877
Tom, what's wrong with your phone?

85
00:08:02,961 --> 00:08:04,942
I've been trying to reach you all day.

86
00:08:04,994 --> 00:08:07,663
There's a hurricane. Everything's shut down.

87
00:08:07,705 --> 00:08:11,448
- Hola, Tommy! - It's carnival, come on.

88
00:08:11,469 --> 00:08:14,076
- The girl's name is Gabriella! - I want to meet all your friends!

89
00:08:14,086 --> 00:08:17,454
- She wants to meet you. - Yeah, we'll samba!

90
00:08:17,611 --> 00:08:19,342
- Are you coming? - I will. I will.

91
00:08:19,414 --> 00:08:22,146
You better. I'm gonna come and get you.

92
00:08:22,157 --> 00:08:23,283
- Tom? - What's that?

93
00:08:23,314 --> 00:08:24,597
I said, are you drinking again?

94
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,963
Nothing like that.

95
00:08:26,046 --> 00:08:29,039
Any time a cocaine dealer is suspected of bribing an agent...

96
00:08:29,049 --> 00:08:32,386
...we pull him off the assignment and run a check. It's not personal.

97
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:35,024
A drug lord that I helped bust says that he paid me off...

98
00:08:35,055 --> 00:08:37,975
...you guys believe him, and say it's not personal? Fuck you.

99
00:08:37,996 --> 00:08:41,228
Relax, I'm sure you'll come up clean.

100
00:08:41,228 --> 00:08:42,406
You'll be back on the job in a week.

101
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:45,618
With everyone looking at me sideways, wondering if I'm dirty.

102
00:08:45,639 --> 00:08:48,110
Look, I'm DEA in cocaine central.

103
00:08:48,141 --> 00:08:49,632
All we have down here is trust.

104
00:08:49,705 --> 00:08:52,479
And after what you did, nobody's ever gonna trust me... Hold on.

105
00:08:52,510 --> 00:08:53,615
Are you putting me...?

106
00:08:54,616 --> 00:08:58,308
Tom, Bill. I need you to come down here.

107
00:08:58,318 --> 00:09:01,175
- Come down where? - Clayton, as soon as possible.

108
00:09:01,196 --> 00:09:03,636
- Something happened. It's bad. - Are you all right?

109
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:08,192
No.

110
00:09:08,203 --> 00:09:10,403
No, I need your help.

111
00:09:14,730 --> 00:09:15,690
Sir?

112
00:09:16,148 --> 00:09:18,588
Sir, this is completely unorthodox.

113
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,954
This guy isn't even Army.

114
00:09:24,594 --> 00:09:25,877
Go ahead, sir.

115
00:09:26,982 --> 00:09:28,129
He was Army.

116
00:09:28,181 --> 00:09:29,537
I hadn't seen him in years...

117
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,591
...until I ran into him the other night in a parking lot.

118
00:09:31,653 --> 00:09:34,010
Trust me, he was Army.

119
00:09:34,521 --> 00:09:36,398
He trained at Benning and here with me,

120
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:38,254
so he knows the territory.

121
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:41,820
Before he left the service, he was the best interrogator I had ever seen.

122
00:09:41,830 --> 00:09:44,979
Tom Hardy could get in your head faster than you could tie your shoes.

123
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,867
Why did he leave the Army?

124
00:09:46,929 --> 00:09:48,952
I don't know and I don't care...

125
00:09:49,004 --> 00:09:51,152
...because there is nobody better in a room.

126
00:09:51,204 --> 00:09:53,488
Sir, if he's not Army, it's not official.

127
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:56,637
Well, then, Captain Osborne, it's unofficial.

128
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:57,919
Evening, sir.

129
00:10:06,282 --> 00:10:08,398
It doesn't get unofficialer than that.

130
00:10:08,889 --> 00:10:12,361
- Hey, Bill, how is it going? - Pretty much fucked. You?

131
00:10:12,788 --> 00:10:14,175
Wet. So how's the knee?

132
00:10:14,259 --> 00:10:16,479
They're never gonna make me a general anyway.

133
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:19,378
Fuck them if they can't take a joke. Why am I here?

134
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:21,453
I'm curious about that myself, sir.

135
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:24,560
Sir, I am Julia Osborne. I am the provost marshal here.

136
00:10:24,571 --> 00:10:27,511
- Osborne, do I look like a "sir" to you? - Not particularly, sir.

137
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:32,881
Captain, Osborne is the closest thing we have to an in-house investigator.

138
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:34,842
And you're going out of house.

139
00:10:34,915 --> 00:10:36,374
How does that make you feel?

140
00:10:36,447 --> 00:10:38,668
- Hostile and uncooperative, sir. - Fantastic.

141
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,556
Okay. Tom, look

142
00:10:40,618 --> 00:10:41,828
before this hurricane hit...

143
00:10:41,922 --> 00:10:44,664
...I recalled all exercises except for one...

144
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:48,386
...a six-man Ranger team and their Black Hat out in the bush.

145
00:10:48,397 --> 00:10:50,785
We're missing three and the sergeant.

146
00:10:50,826 --> 00:10:52,380
Not West?

147
00:10:52,463 --> 00:10:54,518
Oh, tell me it wasn't West.

148
00:10:54,997 --> 00:10:56,624
You know Sergeant West, sir?

149
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:58,813
He was our Black Hat.

150
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,461
That must have been an honor.

151
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:01,712
That's one way to put it.

152
00:11:01,806 --> 00:11:03,985
West is a professional, the face of the modern Army.

153
00:11:04,037 --> 00:11:06,300
You notice I'm no longer in the Army.

154
00:11:06,947 --> 00:11:08,886
They were due for pickup at 1830.

155
00:11:08,949 --> 00:11:11,378
So the problem is that three didn't come back?

156
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:14,538
No. The problem is, one of them is dead...

157
00:11:14,548 --> 00:11:18,083
...one has a bullet in his hip and one won't talk.

158
00:11:18,093 --> 00:11:20,721
Now the one who won't talk was exchanging live fire with the dead one.

159
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:23,192
I'm assuming that's what made him the dead one.

160
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,258
Sergeant Mueller, killed right in front of me.

161
00:11:26,299 --> 00:11:28,896
If Command finds out you're using a civilian...

162
00:11:28,937 --> 00:11:31,920
...with my background, forget it, they'll cut you a new asshole.

163
00:11:31,940 --> 00:11:34,047
Your involvement's a secret.

164
00:11:34,109 --> 00:11:36,090
Anything you uncover will be credited to Osborne.

165
00:11:36,142 --> 00:11:37,383
Well, then, let her do it.

166
00:11:37,477 --> 00:11:40,574
Sir, that is not a bad idea.

167
00:11:41,679 --> 00:11:43,692
Captain, will you excuse us for a moment?

168
00:11:45,954 --> 00:11:49,541
All due respect to Osborne, this is way out of her league.

169
00:11:49,552 --> 00:11:52,471
This kid we have in interrogation requested a Ranger.

170
00:11:52,492 --> 00:11:54,890
Someone he'd never met. That's you.

171
00:11:55,224 --> 00:11:57,205
Jesus, Bill, he could have requested a sailboat.

172
00:11:57,257 --> 00:11:59,134
It doesn't mean you have to give it to him.

173
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:02,116
I don't get this.

174
00:12:02,169 --> 00:12:03,899
Any spooks involved here?

175
00:12:03,972 --> 00:12:06,152
CIA? FBI?

176
00:12:06,642 --> 00:12:08,373
Not exactly.

177
00:12:08,435 --> 00:12:09,864
What does that mean?

178
00:12:10,437 --> 00:12:13,670
There was a group of guys down here and they...

179
00:12:15,046 --> 00:12:16,579
And they what?

180
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:18,456
Come on, Bill, spill it.

181
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,397
Permission to speak freely, sir?

182
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:34,597
Osborne, I swear to God...

183
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:37,548
...you call me sir one more time, I'm gonna scream.

184
00:12:40,134 --> 00:12:41,312
I know who you are.

185
00:12:41,406 --> 00:12:44,075
The DEA is investigating you for bribery.

186
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,734
Suspicion of bribery.

187
00:12:46,776 --> 00:12:48,089
It's all in the wording, really.

188
00:12:48,183 --> 00:12:50,915
I'm not comfortable having you involved with this.

189
00:12:50,946 --> 00:12:53,094
Three things: First, you don't have a choice.

190
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:55,514
Second, I've never taken a bribe in my life.

191
00:12:55,555 --> 00:12:59,309
And third, I'm still a little drunk from earlier today...

192
00:12:59,319 --> 00:13:01,540
...so if I skip over the witty banter...

193
00:13:01,593 --> 00:13:04,470
...and move straight into coming on to you,

194
00:13:04,491 --> 00:13:06,441
I hope you don't take offense.

195
00:13:12,770 --> 00:13:16,107
Dog tags identify them as Sergeant Raymond Dunbar...

196
00:13:16,107 --> 00:13:18,328
...and Second Lieutenant Levi Kendall.

197
00:13:18,610 --> 00:13:21,487
Levi? Who would name their kid Levi?

198
00:13:21,508 --> 00:13:25,742
General Jonathan Kendall, of the Joint Chiefs.

199
00:13:25,752 --> 00:13:28,630
Remind me to thank Bill for mentioning that on the phone.

200
00:13:28,651 --> 00:13:31,810
Kendall Jr. will be unconscious for at least another hour.

201
00:13:31,821 --> 00:13:34,292
The soldier we're talking to first is Dunbar.

202
00:13:34,323 --> 00:13:36,471
- ls he in an interrogation room? - Yes, sir.

203
00:13:36,523 --> 00:13:37,848
Move him.

204
00:13:37,931 --> 00:13:39,286
Why?

205
00:13:39,359 --> 00:13:43,655
Interrogation rooms tend to look suspiciously like interrogation rooms...

206
00:13:43,666 --> 00:13:45,887
...which makes people uncomfortable.

207
00:13:45,939 --> 00:13:47,847
- Is he cute? - Excuse me?

208
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:49,849
Dunbar, is he cute?

209
00:13:50,808 --> 00:13:51,841
If you're not gonna take this seriously...

210
00:13:51,945 --> 00:13:56,387
Is he handsome? Does he carry himself well?

211
00:13:57,649 --> 00:13:59,202
Does he look you in the eyes or down at the floor?

212
00:13:59,286 --> 00:14:03,206
Does he have good bones, which suggests good breeding? Does he slouch or sit up?

213
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:07,012
These are questions that reveal a great deal about a man's character.

214
00:14:07,023 --> 00:14:09,139
Get over yourself for two-and-a-half seconds

215
00:14:09,191 --> 00:14:11,767
and tell me, is he cute?

216
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:14,853
Yes, sir.

217
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:17,262
Thank you.

218
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:19,577
I'll let you know how it turns out.

219
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,799
Agent Hardy,

220
00:14:23,341 --> 00:14:25,176
if this goes to trial someone is gonna have to testify...

221
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:26,792
...about what's said in interrogation.

222
00:14:26,876 --> 00:14:28,753
And with your colorful background...

223
00:14:28,815 --> 00:14:32,506
...you'd be the most impeachable witness in history.

224
00:14:32,517 --> 00:14:34,008
Now, I may be stuck with you,

225
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:36,031
but you're definitely stuck with me.

226
00:14:39,524 --> 00:14:43,726
Okay. At some point I want you to go bad cop on him.

227
00:14:45,196 --> 00:14:47,970
The signal will be my rubbing my nose.

228
00:14:48,001 --> 00:14:49,586
Not scratching your balls?

229
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:52,047
Look for both. Any donuts around here?

230
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:54,883
I questioned him for two hours. He didn't make a sound.

231
00:14:54,904 --> 00:14:57,333
You try poking him with a stick?

232
00:14:57,375 --> 00:15:00,534
Sorry, no. I didn't learn sophisticated techniques like that.

233
00:15:00,878 --> 00:15:04,351
I bet I can get him to talk in under three minutes.

234
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:07,844
Ten bucks. That's without telling him I'm a Ranger.

235
00:15:09,752 --> 00:15:10,784
Go.

236
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:16,498
Sergeant Dunbar, good evening.

237
00:15:16,863 --> 00:15:18,219
I'm Tom Hardy

238
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:22,077
I believe you've already met the vivacious Captain Osborne.

239
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,872
I understand that you've had a rough time of it out there...

240
00:15:26,237 --> 00:15:28,041
...and that you're not talking.

241
00:15:28,604 --> 00:15:31,107
I'm sure you just want to get some sleep and food.

242
00:15:31,138 --> 00:15:32,598
Did they feed you yet?

243
00:15:41,721 --> 00:15:44,318
Go on. You can still eat in front of someone and not talk.

244
00:15:44,359 --> 00:15:46,507
My parents did it for years.

245
00:15:56,069 --> 00:15:57,310
You want another one?

246
00:15:57,873 --> 00:15:59,604
Maybe later.

247
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:03,597
Okay, Ray, I'm gonna be upfront with you. I don't know if you did what you did in self-defense...

248
00:16:03,608 --> 00:16:06,799
...and frankly, I don't care.

249
00:16:07,309 --> 00:16:09,854
The thing is, I made an agreement with a friend...

250
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:14,004
...to talk to you till your transport showed up.

251
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:19,082
You like baseball?

252
00:16:20,990 --> 00:16:23,628
Oh, I could talk baseball for days.

253
00:16:26,099 --> 00:16:27,934
You know, batting averages, ERAs,

254
00:16:27,997 --> 00:16:30,593
I got statistics in my brain.

255
00:16:30,635 --> 00:16:32,887
I don't know how I remember them. It's freaky.

256
00:16:34,337 --> 00:16:35,932
You wanna talk baseball?

257
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:38,851
Oh, come on, Ray,

258
00:16:38,945 --> 00:16:40,228
we gotta talk about something.

259
00:16:40,311 --> 00:16:42,219
We're gonna be here for six hours.

260
00:16:43,512 --> 00:16:46,255
Come on, who do you like? Who do you like?

261
00:16:48,288 --> 00:16:50,498
Sir, I don't like baseball.

262
00:16:52,188 --> 00:16:53,992
Why not?

263
00:16:56,359 --> 00:16:58,267
I believe the game of baseball to be too slow.

264
00:16:58,329 --> 00:17:02,458
Too slow? It's a game of anticipation. That's the beauty.

265
00:17:03,470 --> 00:17:05,649
Well, sir, I just don't like it.

266
00:17:05,701 --> 00:17:07,891
I'm sorry I don't have an adequate explanation.

267
00:17:07,943 --> 00:17:11,686
Well, that's all right. I'm not gonna kneecap you or anything.

268
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:14,960
Sir, I requested a fellow Ranger.

269
00:17:21,384 --> 00:17:23,114
I apologize. I just...

270
00:17:23,187 --> 00:17:25,617
It's just that you thought I looked like a scumbag.

271
00:17:25,659 --> 00:17:29,371
I know. It turns a lot of people off.

272
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:35,116
You know, I was here in the 75th, under Sergeant West.

273
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:38,693
Yeah, he had a wicked-looking blade.

274
00:17:38,703 --> 00:17:40,778
Yeah. He still got that?

275
00:17:40,841 --> 00:17:42,947
Hand-carved. Yes, sir.

276
00:17:43,009 --> 00:17:47,097
Well, the reason I remember is he would use me as his knife dummy.

277
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:49,818
- He ever do that to you guys? - Oh, yeah.

278
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:54,834
What West used to do is he would say that he could...

279
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:56,377
...slice a man from stem to sternum, the stem being your dick, okay?

280
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:57,357
- I get it. - Okay. Well, anyway...

281
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:59,922
...if you're his knife dummy,

282
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:03,519
he would just ram this pipe into your balls all day.

283
00:18:03,530 --> 00:18:05,855
And that was a long day.

284
00:18:07,430 --> 00:18:11,892
By the way, Ray, I promised I would ask where West and the others are...

285
00:18:11,903 --> 00:18:13,561
...and can they be found?

286
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,273
There's no need.

287
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:20,787
They're dead, aren't they?

288
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:24,666
Yes, sir.

289
00:18:25,291 --> 00:18:26,532
You kill them?

290
00:18:37,428 --> 00:18:41,401
Look, we got enough on you to deep-fry your ass!

291
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:42,569
Back to silent treatment, fine by me.

292
00:18:42,621 --> 00:18:44,289
I'm just gonna have to haul your ass...

293
00:18:44,373 --> 00:18:46,656
Okay, whoa. Time-out.

294
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:50,233
Look, Ray, this is what you call "good cop-bad cop."

295
00:18:50,243 --> 00:18:52,913
She shouts. I stand up for you. You're grateful.

296
00:18:52,944 --> 00:18:57,136
This establishes some sort of bond of trust.

297
00:18:57,146 --> 00:18:59,096
I don't wanna play games with you...

298
00:18:59,148 --> 00:19:02,245
...so I say we take a break. Okay?

299
00:19:02,255 --> 00:19:04,017
And get you another donut.

300
00:19:04,090 --> 00:19:06,791
You see if you wanna talk anymore.

301
00:19:09,429 --> 00:19:10,889
"Deep-fry your ass"?

302
00:19:10,962 --> 00:19:12,140
You set me up.

303
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:14,173
I believe somebody owes me 10 bucks.

304
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:16,905
You could have told me what you were planning.

305
00:19:16,937 --> 00:19:18,845
Everybody knows good cop-bad cop.

306
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:20,742
By admitting it, I could gain his trust.

307
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:24,965
You think he did it?

308
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:26,436
No, sir.

309
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,199
Yes.

310
00:19:30,346 --> 00:19:32,254
What about the rest of my people?

311
00:19:36,185 --> 00:19:38,062
In 5 1/2 hours, it'll be out of our hands.

312
00:19:38,124 --> 00:19:40,137
I'm gonna have a lot to answer for.

313
00:19:41,023 --> 00:19:43,693
I'd appreciate it if you could get me some of those answers.

314
00:19:46,362 --> 00:19:48,093
Why did you ask for a Ranger?

315
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:49,970
I'm not telling you what happened.

316
00:19:50,501 --> 00:19:52,514
Why don't you tell us about the others?

317
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:55,527
Tell us about the course. Tell us about Sergeant West.

318
00:19:55,538 --> 00:19:57,488
Is he still the same prick?

319
00:19:57,540 --> 00:19:58,895
I do not care...

320
00:19:58,979 --> 00:20:01,231
that you are triple volunteers.

321
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:04,870
I do not care that you think you are hard.

322
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:10,209
And I especially don't give a rat's fuck what four-star general's dick...

323
00:20:10,219 --> 00:20:14,484
...you sucked to get the privilege of being able stand before me today.

324
00:20:14,494 --> 00:20:17,716
Those of you I deem unworthy will not remain.

325
00:20:17,727 --> 00:20:21,386
Is that understood?

326
00:20:21,397 --> 00:20:22,951
Can I get a"Hoo-ha, sergeant"?

327
00:20:23,034 --> 00:20:24,389
Hoo-ha, sergeant!

328
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:28,029
Those of you I find lacking will quit.

329
00:20:28,039 --> 00:20:33,096
And those of you who refuse to quit will have a training accident.

330
00:20:33,107 --> 00:20:36,485
This base suffers three training accidents a year.

331
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:40,812
Unfortunate accidents that I will not hesitate to repeat...

332
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:44,576
...if you cross me. Is that understood?

333
00:20:44,587 --> 00:20:46,047
Give me a "Hoo-ha, sergeant."

334
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,850
Hoo-ha, sergeant!

335
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:49,394
And what's your name?

336
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:51,437
Sergeant, my name is Pike, sergeant.

337
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,378
Pike, surrender your sidearm for inspection.

338
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:58,726
What the fuck are you doing? Have you lost your fucking mind?

339
00:20:58,736 --> 00:21:00,571
- You told me to relinquish... - Are you talking?

340
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,855
Did you speak to me?

341
00:21:02,907 --> 00:21:05,055
Who the fuck told you to speak?!

342
00:21:05,107 --> 00:21:08,173
A Ranger never relinquishes his weapon!

343
00:21:08,183 --> 00:21:12,604
If George S. Motherfucking Patton rises from his holy graveand asks you for your weapon,

344
00:21:12,615 --> 00:21:15,253
you will not surrender your weapon.

345
00:21:15,284 --> 00:21:17,682
Everybody better give me a "Hoo-ha, sergeant."

346
00:21:17,724 --> 00:21:19,184
- Hoo-ha, sergeant! - Now, son...

347
00:21:19,257 --> 00:21:23,813
...there are people in this world that will kill you for no damn reason...

348
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:26,535
...other than something passing through their mind!

349
00:21:26,566 --> 00:21:28,558
I hail from Biloxi, Mississippi,

350
00:21:28,568 --> 00:21:30,779
where vanilla motherfuckers like that...

351
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:34,595
...used to hang us from trees by our necks on a whim!

352
00:21:34,606 --> 00:21:37,973
Does that sound like the kind of fucking place you want to grow up?

353
00:21:37,973 --> 00:21:39,287
Sergeant, no, sergeant!

354
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:42,958
Are you implying something negative about the great state of Mississippi?

355
00:21:43,615 --> 00:21:47,650
From the beginning, West had a chip on his shoulder for this guy named Pike.

356
00:21:49,287 --> 00:21:52,926
By the time we did Green Hell, it was getting nuts.

357
00:21:53,687 --> 00:21:55,981
Green Hell was 20 days in the Darien at 40 clicks a day...

358
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:58,942
...with an 80-pound pack on your back.

359
00:21:58,963 --> 00:22:01,841
We got real used to number oddities like that.

360
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:03,489
The course was called Jungle Leader and the idea...

361
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:06,627
...was to teach you how to think when you were exhausted.

362
00:22:07,972 --> 00:22:10,569
And West really knew how to get you exhausted.

363
00:22:13,676 --> 00:22:15,407
We spent our nights doing escape and evasions...

364
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,951
...with live fire snapping by our heads...

365
00:22:17,982 --> 00:22:20,579
...or else up to our noses in some damn swamp...

366
00:22:20,620 --> 00:22:22,873
...slapping bugs and dodging snakes.

367
00:22:22,925 --> 00:22:24,760
The nights we did mock POW stuff,

368
00:22:24,822 --> 00:22:26,553
they wouldn't let us sleep at all.

369
00:22:32,132 --> 00:22:35,083
We humped over the Cordillera three times...

370
00:22:35,104 --> 00:22:37,043
...all the way to the Colombian border and back.

371
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:41,860
Some of that stuff is steep as hell and the rain never let up for days.

372
00:22:43,278 --> 00:22:45,979
Those packs got heavy in the rain...

373
00:22:46,010 --> 00:22:49,973
and nobody ever hated anything like we hated those damn packs.

374
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:52,037
There was this one escarpment,

375
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:55,415
it wasn't more than 500 feet... but, Jesus, it was slippery.

376
00:22:55,885 --> 00:22:57,657
Mr. Pike...

377
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:00,785
...can you tell me the muzzle velocity of an M-16?

378
00:23:07,031 --> 00:23:08,866
Eleven hundred, sergeant.

379
00:23:08,929 --> 00:23:10,597
Eleven hundred what?

380
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:13,600
Meters per second, sergeant.

381
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:15,164
Take 40% of that and multiply it by the exact number...

382
00:23:15,237 --> 00:23:19,648
...of each animal Moses took with him on the Ark.

383
00:23:23,277 --> 00:23:24,632
- Come on. - Twenty...

384
00:23:26,916 --> 00:23:28,970
Come on. You tired,

385
00:23:29,022 --> 00:23:30,127
Mr. Pike? Too tired to think?

386
00:23:30,232 --> 00:23:31,743
Zero, schmuck.

387
00:23:31,837 --> 00:23:33,725
Moses wasn't on the Ark.

388
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,278
Have you lost it?

389
00:23:36,071 --> 00:23:37,520
Well, tell me this.

390
00:23:38,448 --> 00:23:40,554
What is your weapon?

391
00:23:41,952 --> 00:23:44,517
Your weapon, man. Your weapon.

392
00:23:44,746 --> 00:23:47,415
What keeps you alive and makes the other guy die?

393
00:23:48,104 --> 00:23:51,555
What is your weapon?

394
00:23:52,608 --> 00:23:54,756
It's your brain, Mr. Pike.

395
00:23:54,944 --> 00:23:57,863
Your noggin. Your noodle. Your smarts. Your gray matter.

396
00:23:57,884 --> 00:24:00,168
Your poise under fire.

397
00:24:00,220 --> 00:24:04,318
Your wits, when all about you are losing theirs.

398
00:24:05,058 --> 00:24:08,176
I think you came to this party unarmed, Mr. Pike.

399
00:24:09,125 --> 00:24:10,960
Take off your pack.

400
00:24:12,628 --> 00:24:14,223
Take it off.

401
00:24:20,209 --> 00:24:22,284
Here, I'll help you. Come on.

402
00:24:38,925 --> 00:24:43,023
You can't complete this march without a pack, Mr. Pike.

403
00:24:43,398 --> 00:24:45,786
I suggest you go back and get it,

404
00:24:45,828 --> 00:24:48,852
even if it takes 40 days and 40 nights.

405
00:24:51,803 --> 00:24:54,337
That business bothered a lot of the guys...

406
00:24:54,368 --> 00:24:58,497
...even Mueller, who was a redneck you felt uncomfortable sleeping around.

407
00:24:58,507 --> 00:24:59,613
Dumb shit.

408
00:25:08,351 --> 00:25:10,895
So that's what we were coming back from yesterday afternoon.

409
00:25:12,928 --> 00:25:15,524
We figured we'd finally get a shower and a hot meal.

410
00:25:16,692 --> 00:25:18,913
I mean, we were the walking dead.

411
00:25:19,497 --> 00:25:22,375
We were about as ragged-out as a man could ever get.

412
00:25:30,008 --> 00:25:32,062
Here comes Master West himself.

413
00:25:36,212 --> 00:25:39,945
What we have here is an opportunity.

414
00:25:39,955 --> 00:25:43,876
A unique opportunity for a spectacular training event.

415
00:25:43,886 --> 00:25:45,200
Dunbar. Kendall.

416
00:25:45,294 --> 00:25:47,755
Mueller. Nunez. Castro.

417
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:49,871
Drop your packs. Weapons only.

418
00:25:49,923 --> 00:25:53,385
Muster at the east LZ in two minutes.

419
00:25:53,396 --> 00:25:54,574
Jesus Christ.

420
00:25:54,668 --> 00:25:56,346
What was that, Mr. Pike?

421
00:25:57,890 --> 00:26:00,736
You think a little rain is inappropriate for combat?

422
00:26:00,768 --> 00:26:05,533
That the game should be called on account of weather? Are you concerned for their safety?

423
00:26:05,543 --> 00:26:06,617
Sergeant...

424
00:26:08,181 --> 00:26:09,172
What?

425
00:26:11,487 --> 00:26:12,623
No, sergeant.

426
00:26:12,717 --> 00:26:15,637
Good, then you can join them.

427
00:26:18,587 --> 00:26:21,194
Those are the guys that went on the exercise with you?

428
00:26:22,352 --> 00:26:24,854
Yeah, and that is all I'm saying.

429
00:26:29,056 --> 00:26:30,495
Ray?

430
00:26:34,426 --> 00:26:35,458
You smoke?

431
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:39,129
Is this a trick where you won't give me a cigarette till I tell you more?

432
00:26:39,296 --> 00:26:41,527
No, I just forgot mine in the car,

433
00:26:41,569 --> 00:26:43,300
and I was hoping that you had some.

434
00:26:47,606 --> 00:26:49,483
My brand.

435
00:26:49,545 --> 00:26:50,932
My lucky day.

436
00:26:57,449 --> 00:26:59,430
You seem like a good guy, Ray.

437
00:26:59,493 --> 00:27:02,402
You carried Kendall wounded to the pickup...

438
00:27:02,788 --> 00:27:04,175
...but I just don't understand.

439
00:27:04,258 --> 00:27:08,460
What did you do to make Mueller want to kill you?

440
00:27:10,535 --> 00:27:12,443
I'm not saying anything else.

441
00:27:17,605 --> 00:27:20,316
I just don't understand why he asked for a Ranger.

442
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:23,215
The man's in trouble.

443
00:27:23,277 --> 00:27:25,154
Never leave a man behind.

444
00:27:25,217 --> 00:27:26,426
So?

445
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,699
Ranger code.

446
00:27:29,085 --> 00:27:31,066
Never leave a man behind.

447
00:27:32,620 --> 00:27:34,080
What's the matter?

448
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:39,460
This place gives me the willies.

449
00:27:39,825 --> 00:27:41,379
Not the happiest of memories, huh?

450
00:27:41,462 --> 00:27:42,849
No.

451
00:27:45,831 --> 00:27:47,040
He's the son of a general,

452
00:27:47,134 --> 00:27:49,428
so go easy on him. Kid gloves.

453
00:27:49,470 --> 00:27:51,170
I mean it. Kid gloves.

454
00:27:51,243 --> 00:27:52,629
I got it.

455
00:27:53,620 --> 00:27:56,352
Yeah. Thanks.

456
00:27:56,946 --> 00:27:58,886
Tommy, that you?

457
00:27:58,948 --> 00:28:01,002
Pete Vilmer, as I live and breathe. How are you?

458
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:03,129
- How are you? - I'm good.

459
00:28:03,182 --> 00:28:04,912
Osborne, Pete Vilmer.

460
00:28:04,985 --> 00:28:07,488
I know. Let me guess, you two trained together?

461
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:08,906
Guilty as charged, Julie-bird.

462
00:28:08,989 --> 00:28:11,805
What are you doing here? You're not getting all nostalgic on me?

463
00:28:11,826 --> 00:28:13,077
No, I can't tell you...

464
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,787
- I'm running this joint. - No.

465
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:19,594
Yeah. We're busy as hell too. Packing up supplies getting ready for the move stateside.

466
00:28:19,604 --> 00:28:22,524
Who'd have thunk it? Pete Vilmer, bettering society.

467
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:23,608
Shall we see Kendall or would you like to continue...

468
00:28:23,702 --> 00:28:26,726
...the backslapping for a couple of minutes?

469
00:28:27,143 --> 00:28:29,364
"Julie-bird."

470
00:28:29,416 --> 00:28:32,742
Now if I were a smart man, and I am not...

471
00:28:32,753 --> 00:28:38,164
...I could come to the conclusion that you two saw each other socially.

472
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:42,752
Oh, I've seen you around the base before, but...

473
00:28:43,962 --> 00:28:48,550
...well, are you in the Army or...?

474
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:49,572
Coast Guard.

475
00:28:49,666 --> 00:28:51,501
We're worried about Florida beaches.

476
00:28:51,563 --> 00:28:53,711
Oh, I've seen you before.

477
00:28:53,774 --> 00:28:55,984
You were in the newspaper.

478
00:28:56,037 --> 00:28:59,603
You're that DEA agent with friends in low places.

479
00:28:59,613 --> 00:29:02,001
Oh, the price of fame.

480
00:29:02,043 --> 00:29:05,139
We were wondering if you'd answer a few questions for us?

481
00:29:06,349 --> 00:29:11,646
Oh, no. I'm really fatigued. I feel all drugged-up.

482
00:29:11,656 --> 00:29:14,117
Our collective hearts weep.

483
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:17,568
Well, we just wanna know what happened out there.

484
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:20,134
Oh, you wanna know what happened?

485
00:29:21,166 --> 00:29:24,117
Well, there are degrees of truth, captain.

486
00:29:24,138 --> 00:29:26,807
You know, there are always degrees

487
00:29:26,838 --> 00:29:28,256
and things are not what they seem.

488
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:29,945
You know, this is...

489
00:29:30,342 --> 00:29:33,084
It is too late and I am too tired to give a shit...

490
00:29:33,105 --> 00:29:36,567
...about some pissant lieutenant's bad version of intrigue.

491
00:29:36,577 --> 00:29:38,944
You're trying too hard, Levi.

492
00:29:38,986 --> 00:29:40,404
You know how I can tell?

493
00:29:40,487 --> 00:29:41,832
Because you're sweating, and you're sweating...

494
00:29:41,916 --> 00:29:46,045
...because you don't know how much Dunbar told us already.

495
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:50,070
Excuse me.

496
00:29:54,595 --> 00:29:56,086
Those were kid gloves?

497
00:29:56,170 --> 00:29:58,245
I thought I did pretty well up till the end.

498
00:29:58,297 --> 00:30:00,872
You mean when you yelled at him and walked out?

499
00:30:00,903 --> 00:30:03,083
Well, that would be the end, yeah.

500
00:30:03,437 --> 00:30:05,272
We'll play it differently when we go back.

501
00:30:05,335 --> 00:30:07,702
Go back? We just blew it.

502
00:30:09,308 --> 00:30:11,007
I thought you didn't have any cigarettes.

503
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:12,467
I lied.

504
00:30:12,551 --> 00:30:14,657
Will you just wait? Just wait.

505
00:30:14,719 --> 00:30:16,033
For what?

506
00:30:17,420 --> 00:30:20,413
Excuse me. A patient is asking for you.

507
00:30:21,424 --> 00:30:22,665
Shall we?

508
00:30:25,230 --> 00:30:28,285
My father is what you would call a very powerful man.

509
00:30:28,295 --> 00:30:29,651
So we've heard.

510
00:30:30,099 --> 00:30:34,958
Oh, come on, you know...you don't know the half of it. I mean...

511
00:30:34,969 --> 00:30:40,234
You know, all my life he's made me feel weak

512
00:30:40,245 --> 00:30:42,455
and insignificant.

513
00:30:43,582 --> 00:30:48,576
Yeah, I think that is reason why I joined the military in the first place.

514
00:30:48,587 --> 00:30:50,641
And how is that going for you?

515
00:30:51,016 --> 00:30:52,267
Oh, it's horrible.

516
00:30:52,351 --> 00:30:54,426
I fucking hate the military.

517
00:30:55,020 --> 00:30:57,314
You're terrified of him, aren't you?

518
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:02,288
No, no, we just hate each other.

519
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:08,523
You know, and normally he wouldn't lift a finger

520
00:31:08,534 --> 00:31:11,975
to do anything for me...

521
00:31:12,809 --> 00:31:16,177
...but the one thing he cannot stand is a scandal...

522
00:31:16,177 --> 00:31:23,038
...and you know, a joint chief with a homosexual son in the military

523
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:25,123
definitely qualifies as scandal.

524
00:31:25,186 --> 00:31:27,824
Well, that blows "Don't ask, don't tell" out of the water.

525
00:31:27,855 --> 00:31:32,307
So is this family history lesson coming to a point?

526
00:31:32,797 --> 00:31:37,907
About four months ago, I began a relationship with a local...

527
00:31:40,003 --> 00:31:43,026
...and my father decided to intercede.

528
00:31:43,037 --> 00:31:49,105
And Colonel Styles made the incident quiet.

529
00:31:49,116 --> 00:31:53,401
But according to my fathe transferred me into West's training course.

530
00:31:53,412 --> 00:31:56,571
And, you know, West just hated that.

531
00:31:56,582 --> 00:31:59,428
He made sure everyone knew where I was and all that.

532
00:31:59,449 --> 00:32:03,245
Couldn't kick you out so he wanted you to quit on your own.

533
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,372
Well, he wanted more than that.

534
00:32:06,060 --> 00:32:08,834
More intrigue, Levi?

535
00:32:09,668 --> 00:32:11,294
Yes.

536
00:32:12,838 --> 00:32:16,550
I swear to God, you will swim the canal!

537
00:32:17,175 --> 00:32:19,751
The teams are as follows...

538
00:32:19,772 --> 00:32:23,431
Dunbar and...

539
00:32:23,442 --> 00:32:25,590
...Mueller.

540
00:32:26,414 --> 00:32:30,793
Pike and Nunez.

541
00:32:31,116 --> 00:32:34,724
Kendall and Castro.

542
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,341
You have one minute to touch down.

543
00:32:37,393 --> 00:32:40,490
Get your shit together!

544
00:32:41,533 --> 00:32:44,129
That's when he did it.

545
00:32:49,541 --> 00:32:52,283
He was threatening my life. It was clear as day.

546
00:32:53,743 --> 00:32:55,922
Did anyone else see or hear this?

547
00:32:56,746 --> 00:33:00,114
No, of course not. There was a helicopter, you know?

548
00:33:00,114 --> 00:33:01,991
Nobody could hear anything.

549
00:33:02,053 --> 00:33:04,942
I don't know how familiar you are with investigative work,

550
00:33:04,952 --> 00:33:07,246
but there's this thing called motive.

551
00:33:07,288 --> 00:33:09,363
And you just gave yourself one.

552
00:33:09,425 --> 00:33:14,420
Well, you wanted to know what happened and I'm telling you the truth.

553
00:33:14,430 --> 00:33:16,411
What happened to degrees?

554
00:33:19,435 --> 00:33:21,312
I didn't kill him.

555
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:24,868
Then who did?

556
00:33:28,476 --> 00:33:30,624
Thirty seconds to LZ.

557
00:33:30,676 --> 00:33:34,607
Click in! On the skids! Lose the communicators!

558
00:33:35,952 --> 00:33:37,266
I did want to tell someone,

559
00:33:37,349 --> 00:33:39,403
but Mueller would've just laughed...

560
00:33:39,455 --> 00:33:42,333
...and Nunez wouldn't have given a shit.

561
00:33:42,354 --> 00:33:44,377
I suppose neither would Pike or Dunbar.

562
00:33:46,066 --> 00:33:48,600
Of course, West had me paired with Castro...

563
00:33:48,631 --> 00:33:51,259
...who treated me like a leper from the day that I met him.

564
00:33:53,407 --> 00:33:56,493
I started getting it in my head that maybe West had paid him.

565
00:33:56,504 --> 00:33:59,601
Maybe he was the one who was supposed to give me a training accident.

566
00:34:35,282 --> 00:34:37,148
All I could think of was West was out here...

567
00:34:37,211 --> 00:34:40,099
...somewhere in this godforsaken swamp...

568
00:34:41,048 --> 00:34:44,833
...making us stalk around in this hurricane, and just waiting.

569
00:34:54,833 --> 00:34:57,982
Hey! What the fuck are you doing? Huh?

570
00:34:58,503 --> 00:35:00,026
This is fucking ridiculous!

571
00:35:00,099 --> 00:35:01,871
Shut up and shoot something!

572
00:35:24,821 --> 00:35:27,261
I was terrified, and I wasn't about to be...

573
00:35:27,292 --> 00:35:29,482
...the victim of some discriminative hate crime.

574
00:35:31,703 --> 00:35:34,998
You know, maybe I should say I wasn't scared at all, but I was.

575
00:35:34,998 --> 00:35:37,782
I was terrified.

576
00:35:37,803 --> 00:35:41,567
You know, enough to want to murder somebody.

577
00:35:41,577 --> 00:35:43,131
But you didn't.

578
00:35:53,454 --> 00:35:54,559
Come on!

579
00:35:55,529 --> 00:35:56,843
Come on!

580
00:36:27,759 --> 00:36:29,177
Is that West?

581
00:36:37,331 --> 00:36:39,166
Whose area is this?

582
00:36:54,817 --> 00:36:56,517
West.

583
00:36:57,382 --> 00:36:58,769
What did you do?

584
00:36:58,853 --> 00:37:01,032
We found him like this.

585
00:37:03,753 --> 00:37:05,380
You kill him?

586
00:37:05,964 --> 00:37:08,112
We found him like this.

587
00:37:08,633 --> 00:37:10,291
Where's Pike?

588
00:37:14,837 --> 00:37:16,641
Come on, tell me! Where's Pike?

589
00:37:16,704 --> 00:37:20,896
- We got separated. - Yeah?

590
00:37:20,906 --> 00:37:23,617
- Yeah, we did. - Before or after the explosion?

591
00:37:29,185 --> 00:37:31,364
Before or after the explosion?

592
00:37:33,116 --> 00:37:35,619
- I don't know. - What do you mean?

593
00:37:35,660 --> 00:37:37,318
I mean, I don't fucking know, okay?

594
00:37:37,391 --> 00:37:39,341
We got separated, so shut the fuck up!

595
00:37:39,393 --> 00:37:40,707
Shut up!

596
00:37:40,790 --> 00:37:43,011
Exercise over! Get out of here!

597
00:37:48,507 --> 00:37:49,998
Radio's had it.

598
00:37:51,510 --> 00:37:52,573
Are we gonna leave him like this?

599
00:37:52,677 --> 00:37:53,949
We have to.

600
00:37:54,043 --> 00:37:56,921
The MPs will secure the site till the CID gets here.

601
00:37:56,942 --> 00:37:59,862
- What about Pike? - I'm not waiting for Pike.

602
00:37:59,882 --> 00:38:01,989
You can if you want.

603
00:38:02,051 --> 00:38:04,554
Fucking do something, okay?

604
00:38:34,417 --> 00:38:35,835
Where you been?

605
00:38:36,388 --> 00:38:37,775
You guys all right?

606
00:38:38,181 --> 00:38:39,850
Where's Pike?

607
00:38:42,091 --> 00:38:42,988
West is dead.

608
00:38:43,092 --> 00:38:44,677
- What? - What happened?

609
00:38:44,761 --> 00:38:47,159
He took a phosphorus grenade in the back.

610
00:38:47,190 --> 00:38:49,213
- Are you kidding me? - No.

611
00:38:49,265 --> 00:38:51,027
He's out there smoldering.

612
00:38:51,736 --> 00:38:53,718
How long have you guys been here?

613
00:38:53,770 --> 00:38:55,709
Ten minutes.

614
00:38:55,772 --> 00:38:59,035
We finished the course, and just before we got here we heard an explosion.

615
00:38:59,035 --> 00:39:00,912
That's your story?

616
00:39:00,975 --> 00:39:03,123
- Yeah, that's our story, Nunez. - Watch it, motherfucker!

617
00:39:05,344 --> 00:39:06,553
Hey! Hey! Stop!

618
00:39:08,660 --> 00:39:10,328
What?

619
00:39:11,725 --> 00:39:14,707
Hey, calm down! Everybody just calm down!

620
00:39:15,594 --> 00:39:17,700
Where the hell is Pike?

621
00:39:17,762 --> 00:39:19,222
We got separated, okay?

622
00:39:19,295 --> 00:39:20,849
She just doesn't remember if it was before or after the explosion.

623
00:39:20,932 --> 00:39:23,039
Before the explosion, all right?

624
00:39:23,101 --> 00:39:23,643
Before

625
00:39:24,769 --> 00:39:26,813
Oh, so now you remember? Now?

626
00:39:26,865 --> 00:39:30,567
Now you remember? Before the explosion. Hear me?

627
00:39:30,577 --> 00:39:31,745
So you think Pike did it?

628
00:39:31,839 --> 00:39:35,134
Does anybody know the shit that we are in, how fucked we all are?

629
00:39:41,286 --> 00:39:43,434
Let me see your grenade, Nunez.

630
00:39:43,486 --> 00:39:45,498
- Yeah, let's see it, Nunez. - Nunez?

631
00:39:45,551 --> 00:39:47,250
Let's see that.

632
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:51,588
Get off! Fuck off.

633
00:39:51,630 --> 00:39:54,747
This is bullshit, man. This is so bullshit.

634
00:39:55,331 --> 00:39:56,864
I'm so sick of you guys.

635
00:39:56,927 --> 00:39:58,209
Okay.

636
00:39:58,803 --> 00:40:00,816
Are you happy now? Here it is.

637
00:40:00,868 --> 00:40:02,922
One. Here it is. You see it?

638
00:40:02,974 --> 00:40:04,914
So sorry to disappoint you.

639
00:40:04,976 --> 00:40:06,916
You're not gonna have a strip-search tonight.

640
00:40:06,978 --> 00:40:08,501
The man is fucking dead, all right?

641
00:40:08,574 --> 00:40:10,106
So, what happened?

642
00:40:14,110 --> 00:40:16,196
Must be a level three out there.

643
00:40:16,248 --> 00:40:18,125
You okay?

644
00:40:18,187 --> 00:40:19,574
Yeah.

645
00:40:19,658 --> 00:40:22,504
Pike, you got your grenade?

646
00:40:22,525 --> 00:40:24,079
No, I used it.

647
00:40:27,165 --> 00:40:29,240
You know West is dead?

648
00:40:30,700 --> 00:40:32,055
Of course I do.

649
00:40:33,932 --> 00:40:35,590
I killed him.

650
00:40:36,706 --> 00:40:37,915
He admitted it?

651
00:40:38,009 --> 00:40:40,157
He thought we would all be on board.

652
00:40:40,209 --> 00:40:43,504
He was that type of guy, I guess.

653
00:40:44,182 --> 00:40:48,468
You know, apparently, Pike wasn't even his real name.

654
00:40:48,478 --> 00:40:50,741
- He changed it... - Come on, come on, focus, Levi.

655
00:40:50,783 --> 00:40:54,213
Okay, fine. So then Mueller went after him...

656
00:40:54,223 --> 00:40:57,748
...and we had to pull him back and calm him down...

657
00:40:57,758 --> 00:41:00,052
...and we said that we would turn Pike in.

658
00:41:00,094 --> 00:41:01,752
So then everybody agreed...

659
00:41:03,566 --> 00:41:05,099
Kendall!

660
00:41:06,371 --> 00:41:07,831
Come here.

661
00:41:11,877 --> 00:41:13,263
Come here!

662
00:41:16,673 --> 00:41:18,175
Come here.

663
00:41:23,253 --> 00:41:26,130
Don't tell me that you ain't glad that West is dead.

664
00:41:26,683 --> 00:41:28,768
Now we got a opportunity here.

665
00:41:30,989 --> 00:41:32,303
- I don't know what you're talking about. - What I'm talking about...

666
00:41:32,397 --> 00:41:37,089
...is we can all walk out of here heroes. All right?

667
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:41,396
Now, all we gotta do is get rid of Mueller and Nunez.

668
00:41:41,406 --> 00:41:43,512
We get the other guys to play along...

669
00:41:43,575 --> 00:41:48,132
...and we can be the men that took down our sergeant's killers.

670
00:41:48,142 --> 00:41:53,460
All we gotta do is tell the story right.

671
00:41:55,285 --> 00:41:57,088
You're out of your mind.

672
00:42:03,293 --> 00:42:06,660
After I woke up, I saw Pike and Dunbar talking.

673
00:42:43,531 --> 00:42:44,740
No! No!

674
00:42:47,545 --> 00:42:49,672
You sack of shit!

675
00:43:13,561 --> 00:43:15,396
It was just a reflex.

676
00:43:15,458 --> 00:43:17,408
Castro had already been hit.

677
00:43:17,794 --> 00:43:20,401
I must've passed out, because the next thing I knew...

678
00:43:27,272 --> 00:43:29,566
Mueller was chasing Dunbar?

679
00:43:29,608 --> 00:43:32,006
Because he had shot Castro.

680
00:43:32,048 --> 00:43:33,810
Why did he carry you out?

681
00:43:33,883 --> 00:43:34,947
I don't know.

682
00:43:35,051 --> 00:43:38,315
Maybe he wanted somebody to cover for him.

683
00:43:38,982 --> 00:43:40,442
But I can't.

684
00:43:41,120 --> 00:43:42,923
I know what I saw.

685
00:43:42,986 --> 00:43:45,009
And he killed those men.

686
00:43:46,792 --> 00:43:48,940
And you'll testify to this?

687
00:43:49,367 --> 00:43:50,754
Of course.

688
00:43:52,767 --> 00:43:55,300
Okay. That's it.

689
00:43:56,041 --> 00:43:57,532
Agent Hardy?

690
00:43:59,138 --> 00:44:01,160
What did Dunbar say to you?

691
00:44:03,507 --> 00:44:04,966
Let's go have a beer.

692
00:44:05,383 --> 00:44:07,636
I don't drink beer. What about the case?

693
00:44:07,677 --> 00:44:10,420
You don't drink beer? Who doesn't drink beer?

694
00:44:10,451 --> 00:44:13,120
Me. What about the case?

695
00:44:16,061 --> 00:44:19,981
The case is done, with two hours and 40 minutes to spare.

696
00:44:19,992 --> 00:44:22,953
I thought we'd get a beer and I'd get to flirt with you.

697
00:44:22,963 --> 00:44:24,100
What do you think?

698
00:44:24,194 --> 00:44:26,634
- You believed Kendall? - Absolutely.

699
00:44:26,665 --> 00:44:28,855
Because Dunbar wouldn't tell us everything. Why?

700
00:44:28,907 --> 00:44:30,429
Because he did it.

701
00:44:30,502 --> 00:44:33,172
No. Dunbar came back for Kendall.

702
00:44:33,537 --> 00:44:35,622
I don't think he's capable of murder.

703
00:44:35,674 --> 00:44:36,644
How long you been doing this?

704
00:44:36,748 --> 00:44:38,302
What's that have to do with it?

705
00:44:38,375 --> 00:44:39,626
That means less than a year.

706
00:44:39,709 --> 00:44:41,618
Osborne, murder is basic.

707
00:44:41,732 --> 00:44:43,411
No conspiracies, no grand mysteries...

708
00:44:43,484 --> 00:44:47,175
...no puppet masters behind the scenes pulling the strings.

709
00:44:47,279 --> 00:44:49,730
Everyone is capable of murder.

710
00:44:51,044 --> 00:44:52,889
Dunbar's our guy.

711
00:44:54,005 --> 00:44:57,654
Look, there's no physical proof. We need a confession.

712
00:44:57,800 --> 00:45:00,418
From Dunbar? Forget it.

713
00:45:00,699 --> 00:45:04,005
You're not gonna talk that kid into giving himself up for the death penalty.

714
00:45:04,369 --> 00:45:06,987
- Nevertheless. - Nevertheless what?

715
00:45:07,143 --> 00:45:11,137
Kendall will testify. That's all we need.

716
00:45:12,409 --> 00:45:14,494
It's not enough for me.

717
00:45:17,184 --> 00:45:20,302
Hey, Ray. Had a nice talk with your buddy, Kendall.

718
00:45:20,323 --> 00:45:22,200
Seems you killed a bunch of people.

719
00:45:22,554 --> 00:45:23,493
That son of a bitch.

720
00:45:23,587 --> 00:45:25,390
Well, that'd be my reaction too.

721
00:45:25,463 --> 00:45:26,955
He's lying.

722
00:45:27,028 --> 00:45:29,843
Why didn't you say something? We would've dropped the charges.

723
00:45:29,864 --> 00:45:31,396
I'm serious, goddamn it!

724
00:45:31,469 --> 00:45:35,056
Fuck your "serious." Right now, we'd take the word of a crackhead over yours.

725
00:45:35,067 --> 00:45:38,164
You got something to say? Say it.

726
00:45:39,571 --> 00:45:41,479
Did Kendall tell you about the drugs?

727
00:45:42,147 --> 00:45:43,565
About the business Mueller ran?

728
00:45:43,648 --> 00:45:45,171
What drugs?

729
00:45:46,015 --> 00:45:49,206
He sold them out of the hospital for 50 bucks a pop.

730
00:45:49,216 --> 00:45:50,676
West is easier to handle when you can't feel the pain.

731
00:45:50,749 --> 00:45:51,959
and you figure you say "drugs"...

732
00:45:52,053 --> 00:45:55,212
Oh, that's good, Ray. You know I'm DEA

733
00:45:55,222 --> 00:45:58,142


734
00:45:58,163 --> 00:45:59,998
- ...and I'm all ears, right? - It's not like that.

735
00:46:00,061 --> 00:46:02,938
Then why didn't you bring this up before you were accused of murder?

736
00:46:02,959 --> 00:46:06,338
No, wait! Don't say it. I'll tell you.

737
00:46:07,172 --> 00:46:10,561
Drug charges in the Army come with a 20-year sentence.

738
00:46:10,571 --> 00:46:13,668
You figured Kendall fucked you, you'll fuck him right back.

739
00:46:13,678 --> 00:46:14,919
I didn't shoot West.

740
00:46:15,013 --> 00:46:17,317
I know. Pike did.

741
00:46:18,475 --> 00:46:20,550
You think you know everything, don't you?

742
00:46:20,883 --> 00:46:23,980
You haven't even scratched the surface.

743
00:46:24,616 --> 00:46:29,110
I know enough to know that you've got two choices.

744
00:46:29,121 --> 00:46:30,966
You can sign a confession

745
00:46:31,029 --> 00:46:33,803
and spend the rest of your life in a cell...

746
00:46:33,823 --> 00:46:37,682
...or you can tell us to fuck off and

747
00:46:37,994 --> 00:46:39,590
you'll be hanged.

748
00:46:39,663 --> 00:46:41,884
Now...

749
00:46:42,739 --> 00:46:45,929
...am I scratching your surface yet?

750
00:46:50,841 --> 00:46:52,300
Dumb bastard!

751
00:46:53,645 --> 00:46:56,117
Why the fuck wasn't he in restraints?

752
00:46:56,555 --> 00:46:57,827
Excuse me?

753
00:46:57,921 --> 00:47:01,142
The next time I wanna borrow your balls, I'll ask you.

754
00:47:01,726 --> 00:47:03,708
Tom? Where are you going?

755
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:05,741
I'm done. I'm out of here.

756
00:47:05,793 --> 00:47:07,378
Wait. What about the confession?

757
00:47:07,461 --> 00:47:09,234
Why don't you confess?

758
00:47:09,296 --> 00:47:12,143
The only reason you brought me here was to protect your career.

759
00:47:12,164 --> 00:47:14,312
People are dead and you don't give a shit.

760
00:47:14,364 --> 00:47:16,658
- What are you taking about? - About West!

761
00:47:16,700 --> 00:47:18,097
You're the base commander.

762
00:47:18,170 --> 00:47:20,537
You know what he's all about and you stood by.

763
00:47:20,579 --> 00:47:23,008
It was just a matter of time before someone fragged his ass!

764
00:47:23,039 --> 00:47:24,666
He deserved it.

765
00:47:24,749 --> 00:47:27,450
Now, there! There's your fucking confession.

766
00:47:29,087 --> 00:47:30,505
Hardy?

767
00:47:31,423 --> 00:47:32,883
Hardy!

768
00:47:33,383 --> 00:47:37,752
What about Dunbar? What about what he said about the drugs?

769
00:47:37,762 --> 00:47:40,015
You are incredible!

770
00:47:40,056 --> 00:47:41,589
If someone said "Santa Claus,"

771
00:47:41,662 --> 00:47:43,539
you'd say:"You can't leave.

772
00:47:43,602 --> 00:47:46,334
We haven't explored the flying reindeer angle!"

773
00:47:46,365 --> 00:47:47,793
You fucking coward!

774
00:47:47,866 --> 00:47:49,003
No, no, wait!

775
00:47:49,107 --> 00:47:51,881
You stop right there. I was there!

776
00:47:51,902 --> 00:47:54,404
I was tortured by that guy!

777
00:47:54,446 --> 00:47:56,312
I wanted him dead 15 years ago

778
00:47:56,375 --> 00:47:59,263
And now, I should feel bad about someone who offed him?

779
00:47:59,284 --> 00:48:01,536
Forget it. No can do.

780
00:48:01,578 --> 00:48:02,725
So fuck the Army, right?

781
00:48:02,819 --> 00:48:05,353
- Fuck the Army and fuck those kids too. - That's right.

782
00:48:05,384 --> 00:48:09,148
Yeah, all they wanted to do is serve their country and take a stand...

783
00:48:09,158 --> 00:48:11,067
- ...and protect assholes like you! - Oh, don't you even start.

784
00:48:11,129 --> 00:48:16,082
Don't you talk to me like some recruiting poster...

785
00:48:16,092 --> 00:48:19,825
- ...because I did my time! - Yeah, please. Oh, yeah.

786
00:48:19,836 --> 00:48:22,161
- And you couldn't hack it! - Yeah.

787
00:48:24,538 --> 00:48:26,269
You were like me once.

788
00:48:26,342 --> 00:48:28,918
You believed in the whole honor and duty thing...

789
00:48:28,939 --> 00:48:31,931
...and trying to make a difference. Isn't that what you said?

790
00:48:31,942 --> 00:48:35,456
I was trying to get your number.

791
00:48:35,820 --> 00:48:38,031
334-5644.

792
00:48:38,083 --> 00:48:38,876
Thank you.

793
00:48:38,990 --> 00:48:41,868
You believed it. I saw it in your eyes.

794
00:48:42,056 --> 00:48:44,996
You believed in it and those kids did too.

795
00:48:45,194 --> 00:48:47,155
Now they'll never tell their story.

796
00:48:47,196 --> 00:48:50,345
Never gonna get to expose West for the monster you say he was.

797
00:48:52,462 --> 00:48:54,443
I thought you wanted me gone.

798
00:48:55,538 --> 00:48:57,373
You grew on me.

799
00:48:58,009 --> 00:49:02,597
Look, I'm gonna go in there, and I'm gonna talk to Kendall and to Dunbar,

800
00:49:02,608 --> 00:49:04,724
and I'm gonna try to figure this whole mess out...

801
00:49:04,777 --> 00:49:07,488
...because I care what happened out there.

802
00:49:07,853 --> 00:49:09,406
And I think you do too.

803
00:49:12,858 --> 00:49:14,693
"I didn't shoot West."

804
00:49:15,391 --> 00:49:16,611
What?

805
00:49:18,061 --> 00:49:21,085
That's what Dunbar said. "I didn't shoot West."

806
00:49:21,095 --> 00:49:23,003
West wasn't shot.

807
00:49:23,066 --> 00:49:26,288
Kendall said he was burned by a phosphorus grenade.

808
00:49:26,298 --> 00:49:28,373
Dunbar never saw the body.

809
00:49:39,342 --> 00:49:43,096
Hey, look, I apologize.

810
00:49:47,924 --> 00:49:49,550
You saw West's body?

811
00:49:49,623 --> 00:49:50,833
Of course I did.

812
00:49:50,927 --> 00:49:52,043
Where?

813
00:49:52,491 --> 00:49:54,211
Down by the creek bed.

814
00:49:54,931 --> 00:49:56,182
- And he was shot? - Yeah.

815
00:49:56,464 --> 00:49:59,362
What about the phosphorus grenade?

816
00:50:00,103 --> 00:50:02,647
One went off, yeah, but it didn't touch him.

817
00:50:03,533 --> 00:50:04,878
I thought you knew this.

818
00:50:05,202 --> 00:50:06,192
Tell us.

819
00:50:26,827 --> 00:50:28,485
What did you do?

820
00:50:28,558 --> 00:50:30,362
We found him like this.

821
00:50:32,698 --> 00:50:34,158
You kill him?

822
00:50:34,669 --> 00:50:36,545
We found him like this!

823
00:50:36,608 --> 00:50:37,776
Stop.

824
00:50:38,005 --> 00:50:40,539
Kendall said that only Nunez showed up at the body.

825
00:50:40,570 --> 00:50:42,072
You were at the bunker with Mueller.

826
00:50:42,145 --> 00:50:44,470
He's lying. I was at the body.

827
00:50:44,512 --> 00:50:46,806
We didn't see Mueller till we got back to the bunker.

828
00:50:50,486 --> 00:50:52,009
Where you been?

829
00:50:52,082 --> 00:50:54,522
West. He's dead.

830
00:50:54,553 --> 00:50:55,794
Back up.

831
00:50:55,804 --> 00:50:58,463
- Mueller was alone in the bunker? - Yeah.

832
00:50:58,797 --> 00:51:00,778
What are you doing here alone?

833
00:51:02,133 --> 00:51:05,220
Pike and I got separated, then I heard gunfire.

834
00:51:05,230 --> 00:51:06,482
It was close.

835
00:51:06,565 --> 00:51:08,119
Well, so did we.

836
00:51:08,567 --> 00:51:10,371
Why you didn't come?

837
00:51:13,270 --> 00:51:15,459
So where's your grenade?

838
00:51:24,416 --> 00:51:26,220
And I didn't buy it,

839
00:51:26,283 --> 00:51:28,472
but Mueller still had his grenade.

840
00:51:30,360 --> 00:51:32,612
At least you and Kendall agree on that.

841
00:51:32,664 --> 00:51:34,603
Okay, what happened next?

842
00:51:36,001 --> 00:51:38,107
Pike came back.

843
00:51:40,401 --> 00:51:43,998
Mueller, what the hell happened to you? Where were you?

844
00:51:44,009 --> 00:51:45,813
One minute you're next to me, the next you're gone...

845
00:51:45,875 --> 00:51:48,273
...the sky lights up like Christmas.

846
00:51:48,638 --> 00:51:50,140
Where've you been, Jay?

847
00:51:50,213 --> 00:51:51,912
There's a hurricane out there, okay?

848
00:51:51,975 --> 00:51:55,353
I couldn't find the spot. My radio's busted.

849
00:51:56,313 --> 00:51:58,429
Where's West?

850
00:51:58,481 --> 00:52:00,807
- Yeah, right. - Shut up.

851
00:52:02,757 --> 00:52:04,342
West is dead.

852
00:52:05,019 --> 00:52:06,333
What?

853
00:52:09,263 --> 00:52:11,004
Where've you been, Jay?

854
00:52:12,099 --> 00:52:14,007
I said, I couldn't...

855
00:52:16,937 --> 00:52:21,244
No, no, no, no. No.

856
00:52:22,672 --> 00:52:24,268
Fuck you.

857
00:52:24,977 --> 00:52:27,229
Fuck you! No!

858
00:52:27,281 --> 00:52:29,231
Stop it! No!

859
00:52:35,925 --> 00:52:37,625
We just wanna see your pack.

860
00:52:38,626 --> 00:52:42,484
We wanna see your pack because...

861
00:52:42,494 --> 00:52:44,048
Why?

862
00:52:44,131 --> 00:52:45,664
Because whoever shot the sarge

863
00:52:45,737 --> 00:52:48,365
popped a grenade first. That's why.

864
00:52:48,406 --> 00:52:51,826
A dead body shows up and just put it on the darkest face in the room?

865
00:52:51,837 --> 00:52:53,119
- It's not like that and you know it. - Do I?

866
00:52:53,203 --> 00:52:56,644
Do I, Dunbar?

867
00:52:59,543 --> 00:53:01,419
I just want you, papi,

868
00:53:02,817 --> 00:53:06,080
to show them your pack.

869
00:53:06,091 --> 00:53:07,478
Right now.

870
00:53:17,894 --> 00:53:19,177
Good.

871
00:53:31,283 --> 00:53:32,805
Tie him up.

872
00:53:37,549 --> 00:53:39,009
Ray? Come here.

873
00:53:40,917 --> 00:53:43,284
Come here close, I wanna talk to you. Come on.

874
00:53:46,058 --> 00:53:47,789
We're friends, right?

875
00:53:52,168 --> 00:53:55,557
- Ray, we're friends, right? - Yeah.

876
00:53:55,567 --> 00:53:57,475
Well then, come on, man, untie me!

877
00:53:57,538 --> 00:53:59,759
You know that I didn't do this.

878
00:54:00,176 --> 00:54:01,667
You hated West more than any of us.

879
00:54:01,740 --> 00:54:04,587
Maybe, but not enough to be a killer.

880
00:54:04,608 --> 00:54:05,963
You're the one missing a grenade.

881
00:54:06,047 --> 00:54:08,476
Anybody could have taken that out.

882
00:54:08,518 --> 00:54:11,364
Did you check your pack coming in on the bird?

883
00:54:14,524 --> 00:54:17,860
Look, you know I don't have this in me.

884
00:54:17,860 --> 00:54:19,383
If not you, then who?

885
00:54:19,456 --> 00:54:20,467
Mueller, that's who.

886
00:54:20,561 --> 00:54:21,739
Oh, come on, man.

887
00:54:21,833 --> 00:54:23,668
We were scanning the area together

888
00:54:23,731 --> 00:54:25,608
then he just ups and disappears?

889
00:54:25,670 --> 00:54:27,088
That's what he says about you.

890
00:54:27,172 --> 00:54:30,769
Who you gonna believe, a redneck or your friend?

891
00:54:33,209 --> 00:54:35,117
Listen, check my pack.

892
00:54:35,180 --> 00:54:36,181
Why?

893
00:54:36,275 --> 00:54:39,799
That's a combat cocktail. Demerol and anabolics.

894
00:54:39,809 --> 00:54:41,436
Mueller gave it to me.

895
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:42,979
You're lying, man.

896
00:54:44,251 --> 00:54:46,087
Does that look like I'm lying?

897
00:54:46,754 --> 00:54:49,183
It kills the pain, focuses the brain, man.

898
00:54:49,225 --> 00:54:51,655
I've been using for about eight weeks solid.

899
00:54:52,155 --> 00:54:54,230
After that first night, man, it was bad.

900
00:54:54,293 --> 00:54:56,243
Malnutrition and exposure.

901
00:54:56,295 --> 00:54:59,319
I needed something to keep me from crashing

902
00:54:59,329 --> 00:55:01,477
and Mueller hooked me up.

903
00:55:01,540 --> 00:55:05,429
The way I see it, West knew. He found out and was gonna report him.

904
00:55:05,439 --> 00:55:06,857
- But they killed him first.

905
00:55:06,941 --> 00:55:09,933
- They?  - Yes! Mueller and Castro.

906
00:55:09,944 --> 00:55:12,613
They must've sabotaged the radios...

907
00:55:12,644 --> 00:55:14,073
...and one of them must've

908
00:55:14,146 --> 00:55:16,096
taken a grenade out of my pack on the chopper.

909
00:55:22,821 --> 00:55:24,177
Who popped white?

910
00:55:25,355 --> 00:55:27,722
- What the hell's going on?! - I don't know, sarge! I don't know what happened!

911
00:55:27,732 --> 00:55:29,286
Get down!

912
00:55:42,779 --> 00:55:45,104
You saw West's body. How was he killed?

913
00:55:45,980 --> 00:55:47,606
His chest was hamburger, Jake.

914
00:55:47,679 --> 00:55:49,410
See, that's close range.

915
00:55:49,483 --> 00:55:51,704
You go full-auto on somebody, close range...

916
00:55:51,756 --> 00:55:53,175
...they're gonna be swimming in blood.

917
00:55:53,258 --> 00:55:56,105
Look at me. I don't have a drop on me.

918
00:55:56,125 --> 00:55:57,648
Now, how about Mueller?

919
00:55:57,721 --> 00:56:01,454
When I walked in, he wasn't wearing shit.

920
00:56:01,464 --> 00:56:02,632
I don't know, man.

921
00:56:02,726 --> 00:56:04,008
What don't you know?

922
00:56:04,102 --> 00:56:07,011
This is a lot of shit to digest! I gotta think!

923
00:56:07,606 --> 00:56:09,587
Come on, Ray, man, we don't have time to think!

924
00:56:09,639 --> 00:56:11,172
We need to go now!

925
00:56:13,059 --> 00:56:14,633
Look. No, listen.

926
00:56:14,644 --> 00:56:17,272
Let's wait till we get back,

927
00:56:17,313 --> 00:56:19,044
then we'll tell everything to the MPs.

928
00:56:19,117 --> 00:56:22,172
If we wait, I am a dead man.

929
00:56:22,183 --> 00:56:26,343
I have a black face and there are a hundred men out there...dying to testify how much I hated West.

930
00:56:26,354 --> 00:56:28,710
My court-martial will take five minutes. It's me or them.

931
00:56:28,752 --> 00:56:32,756
I don't got that time. You gotta make up your mind, man.

932
00:56:35,498 --> 00:56:38,418
Ray. Untie me.

933
00:56:42,672 --> 00:56:44,132
Come on, Ray.

934
00:56:50,211 --> 00:56:51,743
What the hell are you doing?

935
00:56:52,108 --> 00:56:53,214
Hey, wake up!

936
00:56:53,224 --> 00:56:55,570
- Hey, hey. This place is gonna go! - Shut the fuck up, Pike!

937
00:56:55,581 --> 00:56:58,052
You were gonna cut him loose!

938
00:56:58,083 --> 00:57:01,149
- Why? - Because I didn't do it, Nunez!

939
00:57:01,159 --> 00:57:02,619
We all know what you did, Pike.

940
00:57:02,692 --> 00:57:06,112
Yeah, where's your shirt, Mueller? Ask him where his shirt is!

941
00:57:06,122 --> 00:57:08,177
My shirt? I tossed it. I was soaking wet.

942
00:57:08,229 --> 00:57:10,106
That's a convenient excuse for the murderer.

943
00:57:10,168 --> 00:57:11,628
He tossed his bloody shirt.

944
00:57:11,701 --> 00:57:14,057
I was freezing from the hurricane!

945
00:57:14,099 --> 00:57:16,278
So you took your shirt off?

946
00:57:16,706 --> 00:57:21,221
I wasn't wearing a poncho, goddamn it! Hey, what about him?

947
00:57:22,879 --> 00:57:24,266
Maybe you brought an extra shirt.

948
00:57:24,349 --> 00:57:27,227
- We have to go. - We're not going anywhere.

949
00:57:27,248 --> 00:57:30,616
Sergeant Mueller, you are under military arrest for the murder of Sergeant West.

950
00:57:30,616 --> 00:57:31,930
- You have no authority... - It doesn't matter...

951
00:57:32,023 --> 00:57:35,350
...because you will be charged with murder!

952
00:57:35,360 --> 00:57:37,967
- Shut up, Pike. - You will be court-martialed...

953
00:57:37,977 --> 00:57:39,479
- What are you doing? - I said, shut up!

954
00:57:39,489 --> 00:57:43,420
- Shut up, you dumb fucking nigger! - You fucking white-trash motherfucker!

955
00:57:44,015 --> 00:57:45,568
I saw you do it!

956
00:57:47,403 --> 00:57:48,988
Jesus!

957
00:57:53,806 --> 00:57:56,756
- Oh, my God. - He wouldn't shut the fuck up!

958
00:57:57,810 --> 00:57:59,540
So you killed him?

959
00:58:01,344 --> 00:58:03,013
Put the gun away!

960
00:58:05,088 --> 00:58:06,089
You too?

961
00:58:06,183 --> 00:58:07,090
I'm sorry, Ray.

962
00:58:07,184 --> 00:58:11,386
Okay. Pike got free. He got a weapon and he came after us.

963
00:58:11,396 --> 00:58:12,533
That's our story.

964
00:58:12,626 --> 00:58:14,566
West was one thing, but this is...

965
00:58:14,628 --> 00:58:16,391
Shut up! Shut up, Mueller!

966
00:58:16,464 --> 00:58:19,237
We have two dead bodies and a story that explains them.

967
00:58:19,269 --> 00:58:21,135
That's what we're gonna say.

968
00:58:24,138 --> 00:58:26,046
You're either with us or against us.

969
00:58:26,109 --> 00:58:27,913
Castro, put it down!

970
00:58:27,975 --> 00:58:29,675
Which is it?

971
00:58:37,422 --> 00:58:39,956
Goddamn it, now we're gonna have to shoot them both.

972
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:23,583
Can I get some more coffee?

973
00:59:27,003 --> 00:59:28,692
Can I get another cup of coffee?

974
00:59:28,765 --> 00:59:30,819
Yeah. Sure. Yeah.

975
00:59:32,508 --> 00:59:35,532
Okay. So the plan...

976
00:59:35,543 --> 00:59:38,567
was kill West, blame it on Pike.

977
00:59:38,577 --> 00:59:41,424
Right. And for that to work, okay, you need a witness.

978
00:59:41,444 --> 00:59:43,321
- Dunbar. - Exactly.

979
00:59:43,384 --> 00:59:47,346
So it's a good plan, but it goes wrong.

980
00:59:47,357 --> 00:59:49,817
Mueller flips out and shoots their fall guy...

981
00:59:49,859 --> 00:59:53,613
...so they have to bring Dunbar and Kendall into their cover story.

982
00:59:53,623 --> 00:59:58,024
Right. And Kendall might've agreed if the hurricane hadn't butt-fucked the bunker.

983
00:59:58,034 --> 00:59:59,588
"Butt-fucked the bunker"?

984
00:59:59,671 --> 01:00:06,480
Well, I just... Well, you know. Happy endings. What do you think?

985
01:00:08,107 --> 01:00:10,161
I think we're gonna need proof.

986
01:00:12,184 --> 01:00:15,437
Ray, you're gonna have to put what you said in writing.

987
01:00:16,886 --> 01:00:18,565
And, Ray? Ray?

988
01:00:18,669 --> 01:00:20,483
For you to have any chance of coming out of this...

989
01:00:20,525 --> 01:00:21,943
...we need to corroborate your testimony.

990
01:00:22,027 --> 01:00:24,164
Otherwise, this is just another story.

991
01:00:32,433 --> 01:00:35,478
Pike said the supplier was somebody over at the hospital.

992
01:00:36,270 --> 01:00:37,824
Guy named Vilmer.

993
01:00:46,343 --> 01:00:50,576
Oh, my God. I haven't had one of these since college.

994
01:00:52,255 --> 01:00:54,465
How long you and Pete been together?

995
01:00:55,154 --> 01:00:57,375
On and off for two years.

996
01:00:58,824 --> 01:01:00,659
Serious?

997
01:01:01,858 --> 01:01:03,391
Semi.

998
01:01:03,464 --> 01:01:05,403
For you or for him?

999
01:01:06,571 --> 01:01:09,074
You don't get to interrogate me, Hardy.

1000
01:01:10,742 --> 01:01:12,504
Know about the drugs?

1001
01:01:14,006 --> 01:01:16,957
Sorry, I gotta ask. Did you?

1002
01:01:16,977 --> 01:01:18,562
No!

1003
01:01:20,283 --> 01:01:22,264
Gotta put him in a room, you know.

1004
01:01:23,182 --> 01:01:24,537
Try and stop me.

1005
01:01:24,621 --> 01:01:27,394
I need that consult report on the chart.

1006
01:01:27,425 --> 01:01:28,155
On the chart, okay?

1007
01:01:28,166 --> 01:01:29,928
Yes, sir.

1008
01:01:31,492 --> 01:01:34,923
Pike said the supplier was someone over at the hospital.

1009
01:01:34,933 --> 01:01:36,069
Guy named Vilmer.

1010
01:01:36,163 --> 01:01:38,739
Well, shit, if it's on tape, it's gotta be true.

1011
01:01:39,271 --> 01:01:40,887
Piece of advice?

1012
01:01:40,970 --> 01:01:43,504
Charming's not the tack to take with us right now.

1013
01:01:49,072 --> 01:01:50,574
I want a lawyer.

1014
01:01:53,618 --> 01:01:55,109
No.

1015
01:01:55,182 --> 01:01:56,736
Excuse me?

1016
01:01:57,747 --> 01:01:59,822
No, you can't have a lawyer.

1017
01:02:00,323 --> 01:02:02,262
Fuck you, Julie-bird.

1018
01:02:02,992 --> 01:02:06,715
Uniform Code of Military Justice says I get a lawyer.

1019
01:02:06,725 --> 01:02:08,904
I don't have to say shit to you.

1020
01:02:16,370 --> 01:02:18,205
How about them Yankees?

1021
01:02:19,206 --> 01:02:21,907
Now, Peter, what I just did is illegal.

1022
01:02:21,938 --> 01:02:24,055
It'll kill my career in the Army.

1023
01:02:24,107 --> 01:02:27,100
And that will end any chance of going to law school...

1024
01:02:27,110 --> 01:02:30,030
...so I don't have anything to lose.

1025
01:02:31,886 --> 01:02:35,879
Now, do you really want to go round two?

1026
01:02:40,196 --> 01:02:42,375
Jesus Christ.

1027
01:02:42,428 --> 01:02:44,336
What the fuck!

1028
01:02:47,735 --> 01:02:51,030
I called them "combat cocktails." Okay?

1029
01:02:51,040 --> 01:02:53,668
I got them hooked, I had them push,

1030
01:02:53,710 --> 01:02:56,827
once they were in, they couldn't get out. It was a perfect goddamn crime.

1031
01:02:56,848 --> 01:02:58,829
How'd you get around the drug testing?

1032
01:02:58,881 --> 01:03:01,280
Who do you think administered the tests?

1033
01:03:01,311 --> 01:03:04,940
I swapped their dirty piss for someone else's clean.

1034
01:03:04,950 --> 01:03:08,547
They could use all they wanted and never pop positive.

1035
01:03:08,558 --> 01:03:09,976
Who else was involved?

1036
01:03:10,059 --> 01:03:11,967
You broke my goddamn nose!

1037
01:03:12,030 --> 01:03:14,168
Who else was involved?

1038
01:03:15,763 --> 01:03:19,621
Mueller and that kid who took a bullet.

1039
01:03:21,571 --> 01:03:23,375
What, you didn't know that?

1040
01:03:25,335 --> 01:03:27,003
How'd you recruit them?

1041
01:03:27,639 --> 01:03:30,006
You know how it is in Panama, Tommy.

1042
01:03:30,048 --> 01:03:31,810
It's easy to spot the bad eggs.

1043
01:03:31,883 --> 01:03:34,584
First week I snuck a couple of them off base. Bought them some drinks...

1044
01:03:34,615 --> 01:03:38,546
...tried to find out which one of them was interested.

1045
01:03:38,557 --> 01:03:39,943
After that it was smooth. I handled the cooking supplies...

1046
01:03:40,016 --> 01:03:43,113
...they handled distribution. That's it.

1047
01:03:43,124 --> 01:03:45,376
Broke my fucking nose.

1048
01:03:45,428 --> 01:03:47,409
When did West find out?

1049
01:03:47,764 --> 01:03:51,132
I didn't know he knew. I just supply.

1050
01:03:51,132 --> 01:03:53,978
I don't know shit about what happened last night.

1051
01:03:53,999 --> 01:03:56,397
That's real noble. Thanks for clarifying.

1052
01:03:57,607 --> 01:03:59,411
How long have you been doing this?

1053
01:04:00,109 --> 01:04:01,976
Gee, I wasn't looking at my watch.

1054
01:04:02,038 --> 01:04:05,928
- Were you doing this while we were...? - While we were fucking? Yeah.

1055
01:04:06,616 --> 01:04:08,347
Right under your nose.

1056
01:04:08,879 --> 01:04:10,380
Riggs?

1057
01:04:11,256 --> 01:04:12,351
Yes, ma'am.

1058
01:04:12,455 --> 01:04:16,980
Read this gentleman his rights and...

1059
01:04:16,991 --> 01:04:18,722
...see to it that he gets medical attention and stick him in a cell.

1060
01:04:18,795 --> 01:04:19,963
Yes, ma'am.

1061
01:04:21,996 --> 01:04:23,800
Nice seeing you again, Pete.

1062
01:04:26,135 --> 01:04:28,002
Why would he risk 20 years in prison

1063
01:04:28,064 --> 01:04:30,285
just to sell a few painkillers?

1064
01:04:30,734 --> 01:04:34,070
Doesn't add up. Kendall's the key.

1065
01:04:35,343 --> 01:04:37,939
Ma'am, colonel's looking for you and Mr. Hardy.

1066
01:04:37,981 --> 01:04:39,638
Tell him we'll be right up.

1067
01:04:41,349 --> 01:04:44,894
Now, look. How far do you want to go with this?

1068
01:04:46,885 --> 01:04:50,045
I think we should go see Bill, hand over Vilmer...

1069
01:04:50,055 --> 01:04:53,277
...give him Dunbar's confession and forget about Kendall.

1070
01:04:54,195 --> 01:04:58,188
So Vilmer admitted to supplying the drugs?

1071
01:04:58,199 --> 01:04:59,690
Yes.

1072
01:05:01,202 --> 01:05:02,265
- Christ. - Now, look, Bill...

1073
01:05:02,370 --> 01:05:06,665
...you know, you got Vilmer's confession, Dunbar's confession...

1074
01:05:06,676 --> 01:05:09,523
...that is more than enough to clear you with CID.

1075
01:05:09,543 --> 01:05:12,421
Great. Good. Good job, both of you. Thanks.

1076
01:05:12,442 --> 01:05:13,652
Thank you. All right.

1077
01:05:13,745 --> 01:05:15,403
Then we'll get out of here.

1078
01:05:15,852 --> 01:05:17,687
There is one more thing, sir.

1079
01:05:19,658 --> 01:05:22,285
Vilmer says Kendall was involved in the drug scam.

1080
01:05:22,327 --> 01:05:24,788
Captain, I don't wanna hear this.

1081
01:05:29,835 --> 01:05:32,160
Well, actually,

1082
01:05:32,201 --> 01:05:35,893
Kendall did try to burn Dunbar with us, so...

1083
01:05:35,903 --> 01:05:38,333
...that usually means someone's involved.

1084
01:05:40,178 --> 01:05:43,932
Captain Osborne, you are not to go near Lieutenant Kendall.

1085
01:05:43,942 --> 01:05:46,539
That's an order. Understood?

1086
01:05:47,884 --> 01:05:50,626
Pike never admitted shooting West.

1087
01:05:51,283 --> 01:05:53,400
You tried to pin three stone murders on Dunbar.

1088
01:05:53,452 --> 01:05:55,360
Why don't you ask him about the murders...

1089
01:05:55,423 --> 01:05:57,894
...he's covered up for his drug dealer?

1090
01:05:57,925 --> 01:06:01,585
Did it ever weigh on your conscience or did you just...?

1091
01:06:01,595 --> 01:06:03,650
Or do you just not think about it?

1092
01:06:07,737 --> 01:06:11,658
Running out of time! Ticktock, ticktock, ticktock.

1093
01:06:12,471 --> 01:06:16,329
Mueller shot Pike point-blank in cold blood.

1094
01:06:17,841 --> 01:06:19,749
I don't remember that at all.

1095
01:06:19,812 --> 01:06:23,638
Don't get me wrong. Mueller was perfectly capable of murder.

1096
01:06:23,649 --> 01:06:26,641
He was the type of guy that you felt uncomfortable going to sleep around.

1097
01:06:27,757 --> 01:06:31,344
Why did you pin three murders on Dunbar?

1098
01:06:31,354 --> 01:06:33,575
The man saved your life.

1099
01:06:34,024 --> 01:06:37,850
Oh, so I should cover up for his misdeeds?

1100
01:06:39,571 --> 01:06:41,927
What? I was just telling you the truth.

1101
01:06:41,969 --> 01:06:43,982
Not according to Pete Vilmer.

1102
01:06:45,911 --> 01:06:51,937
Vilmer. Vilmer.

1103
01:06:51,948 --> 01:06:54,200
Vilmer. Is that what you think you have on me?

1104
01:06:54,753 --> 01:06:59,143
It's his drug-peddling word against mine. You have to do better than that.

1105
01:06:59,153 --> 01:07:01,228
You guys are on drugs.

1106
01:07:02,521 --> 01:07:04,012
They got their story straight.

1107
01:07:04,085 --> 01:07:04,992
What do you mean?

1108
01:07:05,086 --> 01:07:09,048
What Kendall's saying about "the type of guy you feel uncomfortable...

1109
01:07:09,059 --> 01:07:11,697
...sleeping next to"? That's what Dunbar said about Mueller.

1110
01:07:11,728 --> 01:07:14,616
Hardy, they planned this.

1111
01:07:17,234 --> 01:07:20,080
Not bad for hostile and uncooperative.

1112
01:07:20,101 --> 01:07:21,655
You're running out of time now!

1113
01:07:21,738 --> 01:07:23,615
You and Dunbar got your story straight.

1114
01:07:23,678 --> 01:07:28,224
You two just kept bouncing us back and forth, trying to...

1115
01:07:28,318 --> 01:07:30,372
...figure out the differences, killing time till transport can whisk you away.

1116
01:07:30,413 --> 01:07:33,750
You're accessory to murder, you understand that? You're going to jail.

1117
01:07:33,750 --> 01:07:36,253
- Right, Hardy? - If he's lucky.

1118
01:07:36,659 --> 01:07:37,796
You know what? You're full of shit.

1119
01:07:37,806 --> 01:07:39,600
You are fucking full of shit.

1120
01:07:43,729 --> 01:07:46,398
What, you scared, Levi? Is that why you're laughing?

1121
01:07:46,429 --> 01:07:49,860
You think we got nothing on you? That doesn't matter, Levi.

1122
01:07:49,870 --> 01:07:51,403
No, it doesn't. Know why?

1123
01:07:51,476 --> 01:07:53,614
We'll find one of those bodies...

1124
01:07:53,676 --> 01:07:56,106
...and I'm gonna make sure it has a bullet in it that matches your weapon.

1125
01:07:56,137 --> 01:07:59,130
I'm just gonna get your pistol, take it to the morgue...

1126
01:07:59,140 --> 01:08:00,881
...shoot it into one of their skulls.

1127
01:08:01,987 --> 01:08:03,154
What's going on?

1128
01:08:03,248 --> 01:08:04,708
What's happening? Kendall?

1129
01:08:05,720 --> 01:08:07,868
Nurse!

1130
01:08:08,003 --> 01:08:10,766
Get in here, get in here!

1131
01:08:11,976 --> 01:08:13,112
What happened? Suction!

1132
01:08:13,123 --> 01:08:14,895
Give me suction!

1133
01:08:17,648 --> 01:08:20,276
- Get that tube in there! - Hold him!

1134
01:08:33,143 --> 01:08:34,874
Captain Osborne?

1135
01:08:34,947 --> 01:08:36,229
Sir.

1136
01:08:36,313 --> 01:08:39,201
You're relieved of your duties until further notice.

1137
01:08:39,222 --> 01:08:39,983
Yes, sir.

1138
01:08:40,087 --> 01:08:42,934
You'll be lucky if I don't put you in for a court-martial.

1139
01:08:45,124 --> 01:08:46,375
He was dirty, Bill.

1140
01:08:46,458 --> 01:08:48,262
He's dead, Tom!

1141
01:08:48,325 --> 01:08:50,869
And don't think you're not on my shit-list too.

1142
01:08:51,432 --> 01:08:53,340
We found the bunker.

1143
01:08:53,403 --> 01:08:55,551
It was demolished, like they said. No bodies.

1144
01:08:55,603 --> 01:08:59,044
Come on, a hurricane like that could've blown them three counties away.

1145
01:08:59,503 --> 01:09:01,525
What happens to Dunbar now?

1146
01:09:01,911 --> 01:09:05,602
In 10 minutes he gets on a plane, which means you're done.

1147
01:09:05,613 --> 01:09:07,792
You'll understand if I don't walk you out.

1148
01:09:12,182 --> 01:09:13,777
Strange kid.

1149
01:09:13,850 --> 01:09:15,164
What?

1150
01:09:15,258 --> 01:09:17,312
Kendall.

1151
01:09:17,354 --> 01:09:20,451
Even while he was dying he was making jokes about infinity.

1152
01:09:31,138 --> 01:09:32,723
What?

1153
01:09:38,615 --> 01:09:40,074
What?

1154
01:09:42,149 --> 01:09:45,705
Dunbar wrote this when he asked for a Ranger.

1155
01:09:45,715 --> 01:09:47,592
There's an 8 on it.

1156
01:09:57,102 --> 01:09:58,791
I don't know.

1157
01:09:58,864 --> 01:10:03,452
Okay. I'll find out by myself.

1158
01:10:03,900 --> 01:10:04,964
Stop.

1159
01:10:09,176 --> 01:10:10,365
Okay.

1160
01:10:16,486 --> 01:10:18,446
Any spooks involved here?

1161
01:10:18,477 --> 01:10:20,959
CIA? FBI?

1162
01:10:20,990 --> 01:10:22,544
Not exactly.

1163
01:10:22,721 --> 01:10:24,254
What's that mean?

1164
01:10:24,859 --> 01:10:28,717
There was a group of guys down here...

1165
01:10:28,727 --> 01:10:32,158
There was a group of guys down here who were way out on the hairy edge.

1166
01:10:32,168 --> 01:10:35,088
They did covert stuff and they...

1167
01:10:35,703 --> 01:10:37,538
They what?

1168
01:10:38,706 --> 01:10:42,095
They went rogue. They went renegade.

1169
01:10:42,105 --> 01:10:43,607
Dropped off the face of the earth,

1170
01:10:43,680 --> 01:10:45,233
disappeared into drug land...

1171
01:10:45,306 --> 01:10:47,256
...and with their special skills

1172
01:10:47,308 --> 01:10:50,155
cut one hell of a swath through the competition.

1173
01:10:50,186 --> 01:10:53,554
West trained some of these guys.

1174
01:10:53,554 --> 01:10:56,953
And he hated them for what they did, and they hated him.

1175
01:10:57,287 --> 01:10:58,569
That could be what this is about.

1176
01:10:58,663 --> 01:11:00,186
Who knows about this?

1177
01:11:00,259 --> 01:11:03,491
How do I know? They're ghosts, right? They're dead.

1178
01:11:03,491 --> 01:11:06,098
This could all be a story. None of this could be true.

1179
01:11:07,005 --> 01:11:09,633
But the note that that kid wrote...

1180
01:11:11,468 --> 01:11:13,313
...had an 8 on it.

1181
01:11:14,335 --> 01:11:17,224
And that's what this outfit called themselves.

1182
01:11:17,880 --> 01:11:19,862
Section 8.

1183
01:11:20,247 --> 01:11:21,780
Section 8?

1184
01:11:21,853 --> 01:11:24,210
You mean, like, they're crazy?

1185
01:11:27,515 --> 01:11:29,569
How could you keep that from me?

1186
01:11:29,621 --> 01:11:31,175
Classified.

1187
01:11:35,627 --> 01:11:37,682
You son of a bitch! Mister,

1188
01:11:39,235 --> 01:11:41,143
I've had it with you!

1189
01:11:44,240 --> 01:11:46,597
Okay, so are you happy?

1190
01:12:00,256 --> 01:12:01,987
Is that a no?

1191
01:12:09,265 --> 01:12:12,852
Ma'am. Need your signature for this guy's transport.

1192
01:12:12,863 --> 01:12:14,249
Sure thing.

1193
01:12:14,698 --> 01:12:16,752
What the hell happened to you two?

1194
01:12:16,804 --> 01:12:19,233
None of your business.

1195
01:12:19,275 --> 01:12:21,110
Kendall's dead and you're going to jail.

1196
01:12:21,173 --> 01:12:23,081
CID's here to take you to Washington.

1197
01:12:23,144 --> 01:12:25,542
Guess I'm on the same transport as Pike.

1198
01:12:25,573 --> 01:12:28,461
Hey, Julie-bird, you bitch...

1199
01:12:28,482 --> 01:12:31,631
...why don't you go on and get me something to eat? I'm starving.

1200
01:12:31,652 --> 01:12:33,456
What did you say?

1201
01:12:33,852 --> 01:12:35,239
I didn't mean to call her a bitch.

1202
01:12:35,322 --> 01:12:38,273
No, no, no, before. What did you say?

1203
01:12:39,160 --> 01:12:43,195
What, that me and Pike were on a transport plane going to D.C. together?

1204
01:12:44,832 --> 01:12:46,709
You mean Dunbar.

1205
01:12:47,366 --> 01:12:51,224
No, Pike.

1206
01:12:52,006 --> 01:12:54,998
The one that they just hauled out of here.

1207
01:12:55,812 --> 01:12:59,701
The guy that they brought in with Kendall on the chopper.

1208
01:13:00,243 --> 01:13:02,016
That was Dunbar.

1209
01:13:02,078 --> 01:13:05,540
No. That's not right.

1210
01:13:05,551 --> 01:13:08,470
What do you mean? Why not?

1211
01:13:08,491 --> 01:13:10,848
Tom...

1212
01:13:10,889 --> 01:13:12,902
...Ray Dunbar is black.

1213
01:13:35,779 --> 01:13:38,031
Son of a bitch did the whole thing!

1214
01:13:38,083 --> 01:13:40,335
Files don't show race. All he had to do is switch dog tags.

1215
01:13:40,388 --> 01:13:41,555
Where's this transport going from?

1216
01:13:41,649 --> 01:13:42,682
Hangar Four.

1217
01:13:42,786 --> 01:13:45,455
Move it. Come on, go! Go! Go! Go!

1218
01:14:07,227 --> 01:14:08,927
- Sir! - We got company, sir.

1219
01:14:09,218 --> 01:14:12,409
- I need to talk to your prisoner right now! - What, captain?

1220
01:14:12,420 --> 01:14:15,642
- I need to take him back for questioning... - We're not finished with you yet, Pike.

1221
01:14:15,735 --> 01:14:17,633
- Wanna bet? - Let go!

1222
01:14:18,759 --> 01:14:21,157
Hey! Hardy, what the fuck are you doing?

1223
01:14:21,241 --> 01:14:22,868
Gun!

1224
01:14:24,077 --> 01:14:26,767
Sir! We have tried to...

1225
01:14:26,767 --> 01:14:29,270
Come on down, Pike, come on down!

1226
01:14:29,301 --> 01:14:31,136
You wanna talk baseball now?

1227
01:14:31,532 --> 01:14:33,034
I don't think so!

1228
01:14:35,505 --> 01:14:37,351
You don't have any bodies yet!

1229
01:14:37,914 --> 01:14:39,801
What are you gonna do?  You're not gonna shoot me!

1230
01:14:39,905 --> 01:14:41,584
You see what happens when you lie?

1231
01:14:41,761 --> 01:14:44,702
What do you got?! You got nothing on me! You got...

1232
01:14:53,794 --> 01:14:56,067
Hardy, what are you doing, man? Stop that!

1233
01:14:56,078 --> 01:14:58,841
- Let him go! - Stand down!

1234
01:14:59,133 --> 01:15:01,114
Tom, what the fuck are you doing?!

1235
01:15:01,166 --> 01:15:02,720
Stand down, goddamn it!

1236
01:15:23,261 --> 01:15:24,679
Shut up!

1237
01:15:30,894 --> 01:15:32,666
Well, well, well.

1238
01:15:32,729 --> 01:15:35,096
What have we got here?

1239
01:15:36,066 --> 01:15:38,255
I told you he knows.

1240
01:15:38,308 --> 01:15:40,591
Now, wait. Knows what?

1241
01:15:40,643 --> 01:15:43,073
About the other operation.

1242
01:15:43,104 --> 01:15:45,158
What other operation?

1243
01:15:45,210 --> 01:15:46,983
The coke.

1244
01:15:47,045 --> 01:15:51,070
They were sending pounds of it back to the States, using military supply lines.

1245
01:15:51,081 --> 01:15:53,229
Vilmer would hide it in crates of files.

1246
01:15:53,291 --> 01:15:55,961
Hell, he'd ship it in a corpse if he had to.

1247
01:15:55,992 --> 01:15:59,110
West figured it out about a week ago.

1248
01:15:59,120 --> 01:16:01,310
He was gonna go to the colonel.

1249
01:16:02,196 --> 01:16:05,825
Kendall and Mueller must've decided to take him out of the equation.

1250
01:16:05,835 --> 01:16:10,496
You have got to be the dumbest bunch of sons of bitches on God's green earth.

1251
01:16:10,506 --> 01:16:13,353
You think you can ship that shit right under my nose?

1252
01:16:16,606 --> 01:16:18,035
Mueller, what are you doing?!

1253
01:16:19,484 --> 01:16:21,142
Get his weapon.

1254
01:16:21,809 --> 01:16:23,134
Castro, wait!

1255
01:16:26,251 --> 01:16:28,087
- Put it down. - Fuck you, let him go!

1256
01:16:28,149 --> 01:16:29,609
This ain't some drive-by!

1257
01:16:29,692 --> 01:16:30,662
You think you can kill a man face to face?

1258
01:16:30,672 --> 01:16:33,102
- Put it down, Pike! - He'll fucking shoot you!

1259
01:16:33,331 --> 01:16:34,916
I am your objective, right?

1260
01:16:34,989 --> 01:16:36,199
You fire, I fire.

1261
01:16:36,293 --> 01:16:39,525
You're down to four. Well, three. You can't trust him.

1262
01:16:39,535 --> 01:16:41,683
Maybe I'll take one or two more of you before you take me.

1263
01:16:41,736 --> 01:16:45,990
The odds are in your favor that at least two of you walk out of here alive.

1264
01:16:46,000 --> 01:16:51,172
Conversely, there's absolutely no way I should be able to walk out of this bunker.

1265
01:17:01,255 --> 01:17:03,195
This is bullshit! I'll do it!

1266
01:17:14,299 --> 01:17:15,686
So pretty.

1267
01:17:18,272 --> 01:17:19,628
So dead.

1268
01:17:42,192 --> 01:17:45,779
Kendall, what are you doing? Kendall!

1269
01:17:49,199 --> 01:17:52,045
What, you don't believe me?

1270
01:17:55,174 --> 01:17:58,093
Medical crate 8469846

1271
01:17:58,114 --> 01:18:00,815
in Shipping D awaiting transfer.

1272
01:18:01,284 --> 01:18:02,806
See for yourself.

1273
01:18:10,157 --> 01:18:13,734
Vilmer and whoever his partner was must have been making millions.

1274
01:18:15,600 --> 01:18:17,675
Where did the coke come from?

1275
01:18:18,092 --> 01:18:20,532
Fuck if I know. I mean, this is Panama.

1276
01:18:20,564 --> 01:18:23,660
Throw a rock in any direction, you'll hit three cartels.

1277
01:18:24,171 --> 01:18:27,122
About an hour later, Kendall and I found Dunbar.

1278
01:18:47,757 --> 01:18:50,719
Put it down! Put it down, son.

1279
01:18:51,032 --> 01:18:52,314
I just wanna go!

1280
01:18:52,397 --> 01:18:55,463
Understandable. Now, put it down.

1281
01:18:55,797 --> 01:18:57,674
Look, I never meant to hurt anybody!

1282
01:18:57,736 --> 01:18:59,321
Let's keep it that way!

1283
01:18:59,404 --> 01:19:02,105
You surrender, I take you in.

1284
01:19:02,136 --> 01:19:05,098
I know it sounds like a shitty deal, but you get to live.

1285
01:19:05,108 --> 01:19:08,674
I'll go my way, and you go yours, okay?

1286
01:19:08,685 --> 01:19:10,374
Not gonna happen!

1287
01:19:10,447 --> 01:19:14,180
You either surrender or we die where we stand.

1288
01:19:14,190 --> 01:19:15,921
- So, what's it gonna be? - Sarge!

1289
01:19:29,403 --> 01:19:31,728
I knew if sarge died they'd blame me.

1290
01:19:31,770 --> 01:19:34,168
That's why I took Dunbar's dog tags.

1291
01:19:38,089 --> 01:19:40,081
Oh, God! Oh! Oh, God!

1292
01:19:40,477 --> 01:19:42,458
Mueller didn't die after all.

1293
01:19:42,510 --> 01:19:44,491
Came after us with a vengeance.

1294
01:19:45,221 --> 01:19:47,129
You know the rest.

1295
01:19:48,057 --> 01:19:51,384
How'd you get Kendall to go along with switching Dunbar's dog tags?

1296
01:19:51,394 --> 01:19:53,052
I gave him a choice.

1297
01:19:53,125 --> 01:19:56,222
Either go along or I drop a dime on his drug scam.

1298
01:19:58,662 --> 01:20:00,434
How about the bodies?

1299
01:20:00,966 --> 01:20:03,708
That hurricane almost lifted me off the ground.

1300
01:20:04,605 --> 01:20:06,336
But they're out there.

1301
01:20:12,749 --> 01:20:14,824
It's there, just like you said.

1302
01:20:16,815 --> 01:20:18,932
So you'll testify to all of this?

1303
01:20:19,787 --> 01:20:22,185
I don't think you're gonna get any deals.

1304
01:20:22,519 --> 01:20:24,250
I don't want any deals.

1305
01:20:25,856 --> 01:20:27,764
I'll take him now, if you don't mind.

1306
01:20:36,533 --> 01:20:39,129
We should've died out there with the others.

1307
01:20:40,672 --> 01:20:42,476
Did you get what you wanted?

1308
01:20:42,539 --> 01:20:44,093
Not even close.

1309
01:21:04,498 --> 01:21:07,095
Just that one thing that I wanted to ask you about.

1310
01:21:07,136 --> 01:21:08,106
Say when.

1311
01:21:08,200 --> 01:21:10,609
Yeah, this is Hardy.

1312
01:21:10,713 --> 01:21:11,516
Oh, really?

1313
01:21:12,642 --> 01:21:14,686
Okay. Thank you.

1314
01:21:16,041 --> 01:21:20,275
The kid said that West waited till the end of the week to tell the colonel.

1315
01:21:20,316 --> 01:21:23,955
Now, why would he wait until the end of the week to tell you?

1316
01:21:24,883 --> 01:21:27,699
I mean, that doesn't sound like the West that we knew.

1317
01:21:29,054 --> 01:21:30,754
You think the kid was lying?

1318
01:21:33,121 --> 01:21:35,561
No. I don't.

1319
01:21:37,594 --> 01:21:39,440
- I think you are. - What?

1320
01:21:39,502 --> 01:21:41,786
I do. I think you're lying. I do.

1321
01:21:42,265 --> 01:21:44,976
I think that...

1322
01:21:45,008 --> 01:21:47,020
- I think that West came to you... - And?

1323
01:21:47,072 --> 01:21:49,543
And you told Mueller and Kendall to kill him.

1324
01:21:52,380 --> 01:21:55,529
Then what did I do, go and poison Kendall?

1325
01:21:55,549 --> 01:21:57,875
Well, who said he was poisoned?

1326
01:21:57,916 --> 01:21:58,855
What?

1327
01:21:58,949 --> 01:22:00,898
I just found out.

1328
01:22:00,951 --> 01:22:02,066
The hospital found out three minutes ago.

1329
01:22:02,066 --> 01:22:03,776
I was on the phone with the pathologist.

1330
01:22:03,787 --> 01:22:09,084
Golly, Tom, the kid was puking blood all over the hospital.

1331
01:22:09,094 --> 01:22:11,075
You know, gunshot and childbirth just didn't seem to fit...

1332
01:22:11,127 --> 01:22:16,800
...so I took a wild-ass fucking guess.

1333
01:22:19,042 --> 01:22:22,159
Was that really the pathologist?

1334
01:22:22,170 --> 01:22:24,610
No, that was my message service.

1335
01:22:24,641 --> 01:22:28,353
Even if it was, does that prove anything?

1336
01:22:28,363 --> 01:22:31,095
You keep forgetting...

1337
01:22:31,617 --> 01:22:33,494
...I don't have to.

1338
01:22:33,921 --> 01:22:37,174
- What? - I don't have to prove anything...

1339
01:22:37,237 --> 01:22:41,804
- ...because it's not my job. - I mean, golly, Tom...

1340
01:22:42,826 --> 01:22:45,120
I just have to get you to the real guys.

1341
01:22:48,102 --> 01:22:49,864
One-third.

1342
01:22:56,871 --> 01:22:58,404
Come on, Tom.

1343
01:22:59,509 --> 01:23:01,584
You've never met a bribe you didn't like.

1344
01:23:02,616 --> 01:23:06,443
Oh, I see. I see. You called me

1345
01:23:06,454 --> 01:23:10,864
so in case I stumbled upon something you'd just buy me off.

1346
01:23:11,657 --> 01:23:13,461
Crossed my mind.

1347
01:23:15,859 --> 01:23:18,851
Like I said, they were never gonna make me a general anyway.

1348
01:23:18,862 --> 01:23:20,916
This is about quality of life.

1349
01:23:22,438 --> 01:23:24,795
Tom, you've had a hell of a run of bad luck.

1350
01:23:24,837 --> 01:23:27,058
Bounced out of the Army, hanging by a thread at the DEA.

1351
01:23:27,110 --> 01:23:29,435
You're gonna wind up a fucking process server.

1352
01:23:30,040 --> 01:23:34,148
If you lose enough times, what you are is a loser.

1353
01:23:35,013 --> 01:23:38,204
Why don't you cut yourself a break, for chrissake? Forty percent.

1354
01:23:38,215 --> 01:23:40,091
Once I'm up and running again.

1355
01:23:40,988 --> 01:23:43,522
Up and running again?

1356
01:23:43,553 --> 01:23:45,253
This is just a hiccup.

1357
01:23:46,087 --> 01:23:49,799
I can get another three, four months before they close the place down.

1358
01:24:01,039 --> 01:24:02,593
I'll have to think about that.

1359
01:24:21,925 --> 01:24:24,949
And then I saw the gun and then...

1360
01:24:24,959 --> 01:24:27,149
he drew it...

1361
01:24:27,201 --> 01:24:29,829
...so I had no choice but to fire.

1362
01:24:29,870 --> 01:24:32,081
How many rounds did you fire, captain?

1363
01:24:33,708 --> 01:24:37,284
- Two. Three, maybe. - Okay.

1364
01:24:37,347 --> 01:24:39,807
All right, ma'am. Thank you.

1365
01:24:50,860 --> 01:24:52,476
Thanks.

1366
01:24:53,592 --> 01:24:55,177
Now what?

1367
01:24:56,230 --> 01:24:59,525
I'm gonna go home and get drunk

1368
01:24:59,535 --> 01:25:01,548
and try to forget all of this.

1369
01:25:01,600 --> 01:25:03,373
Well, in that case...

1370
01:25:04,269 --> 01:25:05,687
...there you go.

1371
01:25:08,503 --> 01:25:09,785
Your phone number?

1372
01:25:09,879 --> 01:25:12,131
Yeah, I thought maybe later

1373
01:25:12,173 --> 01:25:14,019
I'd slip by and we'd do the old...

1374
01:25:15,249 --> 01:25:19,243
It's just in case you need me to testify about the shooting.

1375
01:25:20,390 --> 01:25:22,955
But you don't worry, they'll clear you on that.

1376
01:25:23,622 --> 01:25:25,207
He was your friend.

1377
01:25:25,853 --> 01:25:28,074
Yeah, but he was a lot of other things too.

1378
01:25:28,127 --> 01:25:30,598
Besides, my friends don't betray their country.

1379
01:25:40,337 --> 01:25:42,036
Tuesday?

1380
01:25:43,110 --> 01:25:45,363
Tuesday, pick me up at 7?

1381
01:25:45,811 --> 01:25:47,688
Tuesday at 7.

1382
01:25:47,750 --> 01:25:49,731
You're one of the good ones, Osborne.

1383
01:25:49,784 --> 01:25:54,226
I don't want you to worry about what happened.

1384
01:26:09,689 --> 01:26:12,244
All we gotta do is tell the story right.

1385
01:26:18,510 --> 01:26:23,474
And we can be the men that took down our sergeant's killers.

1386
01:26:23,484 --> 01:26:26,925
All we gotta do is tell the story...

1387
01:26:26,935 --> 01:26:29,928
Tell the story right.

1388
01:27:41,364 --> 01:27:43,574
...friends in low places.

1389
01:27:45,159 --> 01:27:48,006
...the murders he's covered up for his drug dealer?

1390
01:27:49,601 --> 01:27:51,749
...wasn't even his real name.

1391
01:27:52,438 --> 01:27:54,544
Pike wasn't even his real...

1392
01:27:54,606 --> 01:27:56,139
They're dead, right? They're ghosts.

1393
01:28:04,314 --> 01:28:07,432
West trained some of these guys. And they hated him.

1394
01:28:10,685 --> 01:28:13,010
I wanted him dead

1395
01:28:14,324 --> 01:28:16,274
I am your objective, right?

1396
01:30:29,428 --> 01:30:30,981
Osborne?

1397
01:30:32,128 --> 01:30:34,422
If you don't like the music, just say so.

1398
01:30:34,829 --> 01:30:36,216
Don't move.

1399
01:30:36,602 --> 01:30:38,187
Put your hands on the table.

1400
01:30:38,270 --> 01:30:39,657
Now.

1401
01:30:40,470 --> 01:30:42,097
Who are they?

1402
01:30:42,170 --> 01:30:44,432
They are my colleagues.

1403
01:30:44,474 --> 01:30:47,050
And they're discussing breakfast recipes.

1404
01:30:47,978 --> 01:30:49,709
You knew about the coke.

1405
01:30:49,782 --> 01:30:51,168
Yes, I did.

1406
01:30:51,252 --> 01:30:54,442
You knew about Vilmer.

1407
01:30:54,453 --> 01:30:56,705
You knew about Styles.

1408
01:30:58,019 --> 01:30:59,447
In fact, they work for you,

1409
01:30:59,520 --> 01:31:01,397
because you're Section 8.

1410
01:31:01,929 --> 01:31:04,286
You planned all this.

1411
01:31:04,327 --> 01:31:06,162
And you killed West.

1412
01:31:06,934 --> 01:31:07,998
Give me one good reason

1413
01:31:08,102 --> 01:31:11,220
why I should not fucking blow your head off right now.

1414
01:31:13,576 --> 01:31:14,963
Tom?

1415
01:31:16,308 --> 01:31:19,530
Why did this young woman have a weapon pointed at your head?

1416
01:31:19,540 --> 01:31:20,927
This is Captain Osborne,

1417
01:31:21,011 --> 01:31:23,127
and she has had a long day.

1418
01:31:23,180 --> 01:31:25,578
Oh, I'll bet it was something you said.

1419
01:31:25,984 --> 01:31:27,747
She thinks I killed you.

1420
01:31:29,259 --> 01:31:30,750
He didn't.

1421
01:31:30,927 --> 01:31:32,543
I thought you hated each other.

1422
01:31:32,626 --> 01:31:35,577
I'm not particularly fond of him, and he is sort of a jerk,

1423
01:31:35,598 --> 01:31:36,912
but what can you do?

1424
01:31:36,995 --> 01:31:38,101
- Will you cut me some slack? - Slack?

1425
01:31:38,195 --> 01:31:41,312
Did he say "slack"?

1426
01:31:41,333 --> 01:31:43,585
Captain. Sit, it's safe.

1427
01:31:43,637 --> 01:31:45,504
You wanna talk about slack?

1428
01:31:45,566 --> 01:31:48,872
You take a simple find-out- who's-working-for-who operation...

1429
01:31:48,872 --> 01:31:50,050
...next thing I know,

1430
01:31:50,144 --> 01:31:52,428
there's corpses flopping around like it's raining fish.

1431
01:31:52,480 --> 01:31:54,002
- Yeah, but I rescued your ass. - Rescued my?

1432
01:31:54,075 --> 01:31:56,619
Did my ass need rescuing?

1433
01:31:56,650 --> 01:31:57,787
Don't put me in this.

1434
01:31:57,881 --> 01:31:59,831
You stumble upon a drug operation...

1435
01:31:59,883 --> 01:32:02,250
...in the middle of 10,000 heavily armed men...

1436
01:32:02,292 --> 01:32:03,220
...and you didn't have to be pulled out?

1437
01:32:03,324 --> 01:32:06,963
See now, that's different. I was going to retire early anyway.

1438
01:32:07,828 --> 01:32:10,883
So you found out about the coke and you told Styles?

1439
01:32:12,166 --> 01:32:14,491
Yeah, who did nothing.

1440
01:32:14,533 --> 01:32:16,962
Except order Kendall and Mueller to kill you.

1441
01:32:17,004 --> 01:32:19,580
And you figured that they were gonna do it in the jungle.

1442
01:32:19,601 --> 01:32:20,925
That's why I called this genius.

1443
01:32:21,008 --> 01:32:25,262
Breakfast is ready! Do you remember the triplets?

1444
01:32:25,273 --> 01:32:27,463
Raul's daughters?  This is hotter.

1445
01:32:27,515 --> 01:32:29,204
This might eat me!

1446
01:32:31,049 --> 01:32:32,290
Captain.

1447
01:32:32,853 --> 01:32:35,877
Dunbar. Or is it Pike?

1448
01:32:35,888 --> 01:32:38,213
- Oh, actually it's neither, ma'am. - Right.

1449
01:32:39,454 --> 01:32:40,705
So you're not Nunez.

1450
01:32:40,788 --> 01:32:43,364
No, ma'am. I'm afraid I'm not.

1451
01:32:45,293 --> 01:32:48,421
Right. Because none of y'all exist. You're all dead.

1452
01:32:49,130 --> 01:32:53,061
Well, you could refer to it as bureaucratic absence of presence.

1453
01:32:53,071 --> 01:32:55,845
I mean, we're here. But we're not here.

1454
01:32:55,876 --> 01:33:00,579
Now, he would be dead in the ground if you hadn't saved his ass. I mean dead.

1455
01:33:00,642 --> 01:33:02,268
You are on it today!

1456
01:33:02,352 --> 01:33:04,187
What are you laughing at?

1457
01:33:04,249 --> 01:33:06,846
The idea that you just transferred into his unit.

1458
01:33:06,887 --> 01:33:09,692
Negative. I just transferred to Arlington Cemetery.

1459
01:33:09,724 --> 01:33:12,528
You keep talking shit and you're liable to make roll call.

1460
01:33:13,529 --> 01:33:16,261
So you're all Section 8?

1461
01:33:16,293 --> 01:33:17,752
I told you she was smart.

1462
01:33:17,825 --> 01:33:20,787
No, you said she was... What did he say she was?

1463
01:33:20,797 --> 01:33:22,330
Hot.

1464
01:33:24,103 --> 01:33:27,126
Yes, ma'am. We're officially Section 8.

1465
01:33:27,137 --> 01:33:31,871
And what about the story about you guys being all renegade drug dealers and stuff?

1466
01:33:31,881 --> 01:33:33,122
More like ragamuffins.

1467
01:33:33,216 --> 01:33:35,989
That's been our unit's cover story since the beginning, ma'am.

1468
01:33:36,010 --> 01:33:39,347
And it's a story that scares the frijoles out of the Colombians.

1469
01:33:41,922 --> 01:33:46,250
Okay, so now that I know all this, what happens?

1470
01:33:46,260 --> 01:33:47,647
I get a needle in my arm and wake up tomorrow morning with no memory?

1471
01:33:50,066 --> 01:33:52,078
Isn't that what you guys do?

1472
01:33:52,798 --> 01:33:56,510
We actually thought you handled yourself quite well in this situation.

1473
01:33:58,470 --> 01:34:00,305
We were gonna offer you a job.

1474
01:34:02,975 --> 01:34:05,331
Did she tell you the story about the carnival last night?

1475
01:34:05,373 --> 01:34:07,250
- Oh, don't start. - Shit.

1476
01:34:07,292 --> 01:34:09,502
- What do you want to know? - Miss Festival Party Lady.

1477
01:34:09,513 --> 01:34:11,838
What do you wanna know?

1478
01:34:12,182 --> 01:34:14,361
Don't act like you weren't all over this man.

1479
01:34:14,372 --> 01:34:16,665
Yeah, tell him the truth.

1480
01:34:19,126 --> 01:34:22,244
So, what are you gonna do?

1481
01:34:25,132 --> 01:34:26,519
I think I need a beer.

1482
01:34:26,603 --> 01:34:28,782


1483
01:34:28,834 --> 01:34:30,252
Here you go, colonel.

1484
01:34:31,107 --> 01:34:32,379
Colonel?
